  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Samuel'
      title: The Birth of Samuel
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a certain man of Ramathaim-zophim of the hill country
        of Ephraim whose name was Elkanah the son of Jeroham, son of Elihu, son of
        Tohu, son of Zuph, an Ephrathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had two wives. The name of the one was Hannah, and the name of
        the other, Peninnah. And Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now this man used to go up year by year from his city to worship
        and to sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts at Shiloh, where
        the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were priests of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the day when Elkanah sacrificed, he would give portions to Peninnah
        his wife and to all her sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But to Hannah he gave a double portion, because he loved her, though
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had closed her womb.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: 'Syriac; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain. Septuagint <span
          class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And her rival used to provoke her grievously to irritate her, because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had closed her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So it went on year by year. As often as she went up to the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, she used to provoke her. Therefore Hannah
        wept and would not eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Elkanah, her husband, said to her, \u201CHannah, why do you weep?
        And why do you not eat? And why is your heart sad? Am I not more to you than
        ten sons?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After they had eaten and drunk in Shiloh, Hannah rose. Now Eli the
        priest was sitting on the seat beside the doorpost of the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'She was deeply distressed and prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and wept bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And she vowed a vow and said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, if you will indeed look on the affliction of your servant and remember
        me and not forget your servant, but will give to your servant a son, then
        I will give him to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all the days of his life,
        and no razor shall touch his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As she continued praying before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Eli observed her mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hannah was speaking in her heart; only her lips moved, and her voice
        was not heard. Therefore Eli took her to be a drunken woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Eli said to her, \u201CHow long will you go on being drunk? Put
        your wine away from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Hannah answered, \u201CNo, my lord, I am a woman troubled in
        spirit. I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but I have been pouring
        out my soul before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Do not regard your servant as a worthless woman, for all along I
        have been speaking out of my great anxiety and vexation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Eli answered, \u201CGo in peace, and the God of Israel grant
        your petition that you have made to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CLet your servant find favor in your eyes.\u201D
        Then the woman went her way and ate, and her face was no longer sad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They rose early in the morning and worshiped before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;
        then they went back to their house at Ramah. And Elkanah knew Hannah his
        wife, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  remembered her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Samuel Given to the '
      title: 'Samuel Given to the '
      number: 20
      content: "And in due time Hannah conceived and bore a son, and she called his
        name Samuel, for she said, \u201CI have asked for him from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The man Elkanah and all his house went up to offer to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        the yearly sacrifice and to pay his vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, \u201CAs soon
        as the child is weaned, I will bring him, so that he may appear in the presence
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and dwell there forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201CDo what seems best to you;
        wait until you have weaned him; only, may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        establish his word.\u201D So the woman remained and nursed her son until
        she weaned him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, along with
        a three-year-old bull,[[COMMENT(0)]] an ephah of flour, and a skin of wine,
        and she brought him to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at Shiloh.
        And the child was young. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:24 '
        content: Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Syriac; Masoretic Text An was about
          3/5 bushel or 22 liters
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they slaughtered the bull, and they brought the child to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And she said, \u201COh, my lord! As you live, my lord, I am the woman
        who was standing here in your presence, praying to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For this child I prayed, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        granted me my petition that I made to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore I have lent him to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. As
        long as he lives, he is lent to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  And
        he worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> there."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hannah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Hannah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 1
      content: "  And Hannah prayed and said,  \u201CMy heart exults in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        my horn is exalted in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.My mouth derides my
        enemies,because I rejoice in your salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CThere is none holy like the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:for
        there is none besides you;there is no rock like our God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Talk no more so very proudly,let not arrogance come from your mouth;for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a God of knowledge,and by him actions
        are weighed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The bows of the mighty are broken,but the feeble bind on strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who were full have hired themselves out for bread,but those
        who were hungry have ceased to hunger.  The barren has borne seven,  but
        she who has many children is forlorn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> kills and brings to life;he brings
        down to Sheol and raises up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> makes poor and makes rich;  he
        brings low and he exalts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  He raises up the poor from the dust;he lifts the needy from the
        ash heap  to make them sit with princesand inherit a seat of honor.  For
        the pillars of the earth are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,and on
        them he has set the world.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CHe will guard the feet of his faithful ones,but the wicked
        shall be cut off in darkness,for not by might shall a man prevail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  The adversaries of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be broken
        to pieces;  against them he will thunder in heaven.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will judge the ends of the earth;he will give strength to his king  and exalt
        the horn of his anointed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Eli\u2019s Worthless Sons"
      title: "Eli\u2019s Worthless Sons"
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Elkanah went home to Ramah. And the boy[[COMMENT(0)]] was ministering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the presence of Eli the priest.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: Hebrew can be rendered (2:11, 18, 21, 26; 3:1, 8), (2:13, 15), or
          (2:17), depending on the context
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the sons of Eli were worthless men. They did not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The custom of the priests with the people was that when any man offered
        sacrifice, the priest\u2019s servant would come, while the meat was boiling,
        with a three-pronged fork in his hand, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and he would thrust it into the pan or kettle or cauldron or pot.
        All that the fork brought up the priest would take for himself. This is what
        they did at Shiloh to all the Israelites who came there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moreover, before the fat was burned, the priest\u2019s servant would
        come and say to the man who was sacrificing, \u201CGive meat for the priest
        to roast, for he will not accept boiled meat from you but only raw.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And if the man said to him, \u201CLet them burn the fat first, and
        then take as much as you wish,\u201D he would say, \u201CNo, you must give
        it now, and if not, I will take it by force.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Thus the sin of the young men was very great in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for the men treated the offering of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with contempt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Samuel was ministering before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        a boy clothed with a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And his mother used to make for him a little robe and take it to
        him each year when she went up with her husband to offer the yearly sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife, and say, \u201CMay the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> give you children by this woman for the petition
        she asked of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D So then they would return
        to their home.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Eli Rebukes His Sons'
      title: Eli Rebukes His Sons
      number: 21
      content: '  Indeed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> visited Hannah, and she
        conceived and bore three sons and two daughters. And the boy Samuel grew
        in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Eli was very old, and he kept hearing all that his sons were
        doing to all Israel, and how they lay with the women who were serving at
        the entrance to the tent of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CWhy do you do such things? For I hear
        of your evil dealings from all these people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'No, my sons; it is no good report that I hear the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spreading abroad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If someone sins against a man, God will mediate for him, but if someone
        sins against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who can intercede for him?\u201D
        But they would not listen to the voice of their father, for it was the will
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to put them to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "26: The  Rejects Eli\u2019s Household"
      title: "The  Rejects Eli\u2019s Household"
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the boy Samuel continued to grow both in stature and in favor
        with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and also with man.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And there came a man of God to Eli and said to him, \u201CThus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Did I indeed reveal myself to the
        house of your father when they were in Egypt subject to the house of Pharaoh? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Did I choose him out of all the tribes of Israel to be my priest,
        to go up to my altar, to burn incense, to wear an ephod before me? I gave
        to the house of your father all my offerings by fire from the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Why then do you scorn[[COMMENT(0)]] my sacrifices and my offerings
        that I commanded for my dwelling, and honor your sons above me by fattening
        yourselves on the choicest parts of every offering of my people Israel?\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '2:29 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, declares:
        \u2018I promised that your house and the house of your father should go in
        and out before me forever,\u2019 but now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        declares: \u2018Far be it from me, for those who honor me I will honor, and
        those who despise me shall be lightly esteemed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, the days are coming when I will cut off your strength and
        the strength of your father\u2019s house, so that there will not be an old
        man in your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then in distress you will look with envious eye on all the prosperity
        that shall be bestowed on Israel, and there shall not be an old man in your
        house forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The only one of you whom I shall not cut off from my altar shall
        be spared to weep his[[COMMENT(0)]] eyes out to grieve his heart, and all
        the descendants of your house shall die by the sword of men.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:33 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew ; twice in this verseHebrew Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And this that shall come upon your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas,
        shall be the sign to you: both of them shall die on the same day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And I will raise up for myself a faithful priest, who shall do according
        to what is in my heart and in my mind. And I will build him a sure house,
        and he shall go in and out before my anointed forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And everyone who is left in your house shall come to implore him
        for a piece of silver or a loaf of bread and shall say, \u201CPlease put
        me in one of the priests\u2019 places, that I may eat a morsel of bread.\u201D\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Calls Samuel'
      title: The  Calls Samuel
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Now the boy Samuel was ministering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the presence of Eli. And the word of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was rare in those days; there was no frequent
        vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'At that time Eli, whose eyesight had begun to grow dim so that he
        could not see, was lying down in his own place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The lamp of God had not yet gone out, and Samuel was lying down in
        the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, where the ark of God was.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called Samuel, and he said,
        \u201CHere I am!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and ran to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called me.\u201D
        But he said, \u201CI did not call; lie down again.\u201D So he went and lay
        down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called again, \u201CSamuel!\u201D
        and Samuel arose and went to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called
        me.\u201D But he said, \u201CI did not call, my son; lie down again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Samuel did not yet know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had not yet been revealed to
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called Samuel again the third
        time. And he arose and went to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called
        me.\u201D Then Eli perceived that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was calling
        the boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore Eli said to Samuel, \u201CGo, lie down, and if he calls
        you, you shall say, \u2018Speak, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for your servant
        hears.\u2019\u201D So Samuel went and lay down in his place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came and stood, calling as at
        other times, \u201CSamuel! Samuel!\u201D And Samuel said, \u201CSpeak, for
        your servant hears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Samuel, \u201CBehold,
        I am about to do a thing in Israel at which the two ears of everyone who
        hears it will tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On that day I will fulfill against Eli all that I have spoken concerning
        his house, from beginning to end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I declare to him that I am about to punish his house forever,
        for the iniquity that he knew, because his sons were blaspheming God,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and he did not restrain them. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore I swear to the house of Eli that the iniquity of Eli\u2019s
        house shall not be atoned for by sacrifice or offering forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Samuel lay until morning; then he opened the doors of the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And Samuel was afraid to tell the vision
        to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Eli called Samuel and said, \u201CSamuel, my son.\u201D And he
        said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Eli said, \u201CWhat was it that he told you? Do not hide it
        from me. May God do so to you and more also if you hide anything from me
        of all that he told you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Samuel told him everything and hid nothing from him. And he said,
        \u201CIt is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Let him do what seems good to
        him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  And Samuel grew, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with him
        and let none of his words fall to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all Israel from Dan to Beersheba knew that Samuel was established
        as a prophet of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared again at Shiloh, for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> revealed himself to Samuel at Shiloh by the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines Capture the Ark'
      title: The Philistines Capture the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  And the word of Samuel came to all Israel.Now Israel went out to
        battle against the Philistines. They encamped at Ebenezer, and the Philistines
        encamped at Aphek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Philistines drew up in line against Israel, and when the battle
        spread, Israel was defeated before the Philistines, who killed about four
        thousand men on the field of battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And when the people came to the camp, the elders of Israel said,
        \u201CWhy has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> defeated us today before the
        Philistines? Let us bring the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        here from Shiloh, that it[[COMMENT(0)]] may come among us and save us from
        the power of our enemies.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the people sent to Shiloh and brought from there the ark of the
        covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, who is enthroned on
        the cherubim. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with
        the ark of the covenant of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As soon as the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came into the camp, all Israel gave a mighty shout, so that the earth resounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when the Philistines heard the noise of the shouting, they said,
        \u201CWhat does this great shouting in the camp of the Hebrews mean?\u201D
        And when they learned that the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        come to the camp, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "the Philistines were afraid, for they said, \u201CA god has come
        into the camp.\u201D And they said, \u201CWoe to us! For nothing like this
        has happened before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe to us! Who can deliver us from the power of these mighty gods?
        These are the gods who struck the Egyptians with every sort of plague in
        the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Take courage, and be men, O Philistines, lest you become slaves to
        the Hebrews as they have been to you; be men and fight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Philistines fought, and Israel was defeated, and they fled,
        every man to his home. And there was a very great slaughter, for thirty thousand
        foot soldiers of Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Death of Eli'
      title: The Death of Eli
      number: 11
      content: 'And the ark of God was captured, and the two sons of Eli, Hophni
        and Phinehas, died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A man of Benjamin ran from the battle line and came to Shiloh the
        same day, with his clothes torn and with dirt on his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he arrived, Eli was sitting on his seat by the road watching,
        for his heart trembled for the ark of God. And when the man came into the
        city and told the news, all the city cried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Eli heard the sound of the outcry, he said, \u201CWhat is this
        uproar?\u201D Then the man hurried and came and told Eli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Eli was ninety-eight years old and his eyes were set so that
        he could not see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the man said to Eli, \u201CI am he who has come from the battle;
        I fled from the battle today.\u201D And he said, \u201CHow did it go, my
        son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He who brought the news answered and said, \u201CIsrael has fled
        before the Philistines, and there has also been a great defeat among the
        people. Your two sons also, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead, and the ark of
        God has been captured.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As soon as he mentioned the ark of God, Eli fell over backward from
        his seat by the side of the gate, and his neck was broken and he died, for
        the man was old and heavy. He had judged Israel forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now his daughter-in-law, the wife of Phinehas, was pregnant, about
        to give birth. And when she heard the news that the ark of God was captured,
        and that her father-in-law and her husband were dead, she bowed and gave
        birth, for her pains came upon her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And about the time of her death the women attending her said to her,
        \u201CDo not be afraid, for you have borne a son.\u201D But she did not answer
        or pay attention. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And she named the child Ichabod, saying, \u201CThe glory has departed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from Israel!\u201D because the ark of God had been captured and because of
        her father-in-law and her husband. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:21 '
        content: Or ; also verse 22
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And she said, \u201CThe glory has departed from Israel, for the ark
        of God has been captured.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines and the Ark'
      title: The Philistines and the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  When the Philistines captured the ark of God, they brought it from
        Ebenezer to Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the Philistines took the ark of God and brought it into the
        house of Dagon and set it up beside Dagon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when the people of Ashdod rose early the next day, behold, Dagon
        had fallen face downward on the ground before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        So they took Dagon and put him back in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when they rose early on the next morning, behold, Dagon had fallen
        face downward on the ground before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the head of Dagon and both his hands were lying cut off on the threshold.
        Only the trunk of Dagon was left to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'This is why the priests of Dagon and all who enter the house of Dagon
        do not tread on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was heavy against the
        people of Ashdod, and he terrified and afflicted them with tumors, both Ashdod
        and its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when the men of Ashdod saw how things were, they said, \u201CThe
        ark of the God of Israel must not remain with us, for his hand is hard against
        us and against Dagon our god.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So they sent and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines
        and said, \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the God of Israel?\u201D
        They answered, \u201CLet the ark of the God of Israel be brought around to
        Gath.\u201D So they brought the ark of the God of Israel there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But after they had brought it around, the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was against the city, causing a very great panic, and he afflicted the men
        of the city, both young and old, so that tumors broke out on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they sent the ark of God to Ekron. But as soon as the ark of God
        came to Ekron, the people of Ekron cried out, \u201CThey have brought around
        to us the ark of the God of Israel to kill us and our people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They sent therefore and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines
        and said, \u201CSend away the ark of the God of Israel, and let it return
        to its own place, that it may not kill us and our people.\u201D For there
        was a deathly panic throughout the whole city. The hand of God was very heavy
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The men who did not die were struck with tumors, and the cry of the
        city went up to heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Returned to Israel'
      title: The Ark Returned to Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  The ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was in the country of
        the Philistines seven months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners and said,
        \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>? Tell
        us with what we shall send it to its place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said, \u201CIf you send away the ark of the God of Israel, do
        not send it empty, but by all means return him a guilt offering. Then you
        will be healed, and it will be known to you why his hand does not turn away
        from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said, \u201CWhat is the guilt offering that we shall return
        to him?\u201D They answered, \u201CFive golden tumors and five golden mice,
        according to the number of the lords of the Philistines, for the same plague
        was on all of you and on your lords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So you must make images of your tumors and images of your mice that
        ravage the land, and give glory to the God of Israel. Perhaps he will lighten
        his hand from off you and your gods and your land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Why should you harden your hearts as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened
        their hearts? After he had dealt severely with them, did they not send the
        people away, and they departed? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now then, take and prepare a new cart and two milk cows on which
        there has never come a yoke, and yoke the cows to the cart, but take their
        calves home, away from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And take the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and place it
        on the cart and put in a box at its side the figures of gold, which you are
        returning to him as a guilt offering. Then send it off and let it go its
        way '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and watch. If it goes up on the way to its own land, to Beth-shemesh,
        then it is he who has done us this great harm, but if not, then we shall
        know that it is not his hand that struck us; it happened to us by coincidence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The men did so, and took two milk cows and yoked them to the cart
        and shut up their calves at home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they put the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the cart
        and the box with the golden mice and the images of their tumors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the cows went straight in the direction of Beth-shemesh along
        one highway, lowing as they went. They turned neither to the right nor to
        the left, and the lords of the Philistines went after them as far as the
        border of Beth-shemesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the people of Beth-shemesh were reaping their wheat harvest in
        the valley. And when they lifted up their eyes and saw the ark, they rejoiced
        to see it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The cart came into the field of Joshua of Beth-shemesh and stopped
        there. A great stone was there. And they split up the wood of the cart and
        offered the cows as a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Levites took down the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the box that was beside it, in which were the golden figures, and set
        them upon the great stone. And the men of Beth-shemesh offered burnt offerings
        and sacrificed sacrifices on that day to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when the five lords of the Philistines saw it, they returned
        that day to Ekron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These are the golden tumors that the Philistines returned as a guilt
        offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza,
        one for Ashkelon, one for Gath, one for Ekron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and the golden mice, according to the number of all the cities of
        the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both fortified cities and unwalled
        villages. The great stone beside which they set down the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is a witness to this day in the field of Joshua of Beth-shemesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  And he struck some of the men of Beth-shemesh, because they looked
        upon the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. He struck seventy men of
        them,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the people mourned because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had struck the people with a great blow. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:19 '
        content: 'Most Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the men of Beth-shemesh said, \u201CWho is able to stand before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, this holy God? And to whom shall he go up
        away from us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So they sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kiriath-jearim, saying,
        \u201CThe Philistines have returned the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Come down and take it up to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And the men of Kiriath-jearim came and took up the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and brought it to the house of Abinadab on the hill. And they consecrated
        his son Eleazar to have charge of the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Samuel Judges Israel'
      title: Samuel Judges Israel
      number: 2
      content: 'From the day that the ark was lodged at Kiriath-jearim, a long time
        passed, some twenty years, and all the house of Israel lamented after the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Samuel said to all the house of Israel, \u201CIf you are returning
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all your heart, then put away the
        foreign gods and the Ashtaroth from among you and direct your heart to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and serve him only, and he will deliver you
        out of the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the people of Israel put away the Baals and the Ashtaroth, and
        they served the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> only.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CGather all Israel at Mizpah, and I will pray
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they gathered at Mizpah and drew water and poured it out before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and fasted on that day and said there, \u201CWe
        have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D And Samuel judged
        the people of Israel at Mizpah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when the Philistines heard that the people of Israel had gathered
        at Mizpah, the lords of the Philistines went up against Israel. And when
        the people of Israel heard of it, they were afraid of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the people of Israel said to Samuel, \u201CDo not cease to cry
        out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God for us, that he may save us
        from the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Samuel took a nursing lamb and offered it as a whole burnt offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And Samuel cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for Israel, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Philistines drew
        near to attack Israel. But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> thundered with
        a mighty sound that day against the Philistines and threw them into confusion,
        and they were defeated before Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men of Israel went out from Mizpah and pursued the Philistines
        and struck them, as far as below Beth-car.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samuel took a stone and set it up between Mizpah and Shen[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and called its name Ebenezer; for he said, \u201CTill now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has helped us.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint, Syriac means '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Philistines were subdued and did not again enter the territory
        of Israel. And the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was against the
        Philistines all the days of Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The cities that the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored
        to Israel, from Ekron to Gath, and Israel delivered their territory from
        the hand of the Philistines. There was peace also between Israel and the
        Amorites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he went on a circuit year by year to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah.
        And he judged Israel in all these places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then he would return to Ramah, for his home was there, and there also
        he judged Israel. And he built there an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Demands a King'
      title: Israel Demands a King
      number: 1
      content: '  When Samuel became old, he made his sons judges over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The name of his firstborn son was Joel, and the name of his second,
        Abijah; they were judges in Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yet his sons did not walk in his ways but turned aside after gain.
        They took bribes and perverted justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel
        at Ramah '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to him, \u201CBehold, you are old and your sons do not walk
        in your ways. Now appoint for us a king to judge us like all the nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the thing displeased Samuel when they said, \u201CGive us a king
        to judge us.\u201D And Samuel prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Samuel, \u201CObey the
        voice of the people in all that they say to you, for they have not rejected
        you, but they have rejected me from being king over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'According to all the deeds that they have done, from the day I brought
        them up out of Egypt even to this day, forsaking me and serving other gods,
        so they are also doing to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Samuel\u2019s Warning Against Kings"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Warning Against Kings"
      number: 9
      content: "Now then, obey their voice; only you shall solemnly warn them and
        show them the ways of the king who shall reign over them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Samuel told all the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to
        the people who were asking for a king from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said, \u201CThese will be the ways of the king who will reign
        over you: he will take your sons and appoint them to his chariots and to
        be his horsemen and to run before his chariots. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he will appoint for himself commanders of thousands and commanders
        of fifties, and some to plow his ground and to reap his harvest, and to make
        his implements of war and the equipment of his chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will take your daughters to be perfumers and cooks and bakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He will take the best of your fields and vineyards and olive orchards
        and give them to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will take the tenth of your grain and of your vineyards and give
        it to his officers and to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will take your male servants and female servants and the best
        of your young men[[COMMENT(0)]] and your donkeys, and put them to his work. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will take the tenth of your flocks, and you shall be his slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: The  Grants Israel\u2019s Request"
      title: "The  Grants Israel\u2019s Request"
      number: 18
      content: "And in that day you will cry out because of your king, whom you have
        chosen for yourselves, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not answer
        you in that day.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But the people refused to obey the voice of Samuel. And they said,
        \u201CNo! But there shall be a king over us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "that we also may be like all the nations, and that our king may judge
        us and go out before us and fight our battles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Samuel had heard all the words of the people, he repeated
        them in the ears of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Samuel, \u201CObey their
        voice and make them a king.\u201D Samuel then said to the men of Israel,
        \u201CGo every man to his city.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Chosen to Be King'
      title: Saul Chosen to Be King
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man of Benjamin whose name was Kish, the son of Abiel,
        son of Zeror, son of Becorath, son of Aphiah, a Benjaminite, a man of wealth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he had a son whose name was Saul, a handsome young man. There
        was not a man among the people of Israel more handsome than he. From his
        shoulders upward he was taller than any of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the donkeys of Kish, Saul\u2019s father, were lost. So Kish said
        to Saul his son, \u201CTake one of the young men with you, and arise, go
        and look for the donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he passed through the hill country of Ephraim and passed through
        the land of Shalishah, but they did not find them. And they passed through
        the land of Shaalim, but they were not there. Then they passed through the
        land of Benjamin, but did not find them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they came to the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who was with him, \u201CCome, let us go back, lest my father cease to care
        about the donkeys and become anxious about us.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:5 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 7, 8, 10, 27
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he said to him, \u201CBehold, there is a man of God in this city,
        and he is a man who is held in honor; all that he says comes true. So now
        let us go there. Perhaps he can tell us the way we should go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201CBut if we go, what can we bring
        the man? For the bread in our sacks is gone, and there is no present to bring
        to the man of God. What do we have?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The servant answered Saul again, \u201CHere, I have with me a quarter
        of a shekel[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver, and I will give it to the man of God
        to tell us our way.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he said,
        \u201CCome, let us go to the seer,\u201D for today\u2019s \u201Cprophet\u201D
        was formerly called a seer.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Saul said to his servant, \u201CWell said; come, let us go.\u201D
        So they went to the city where the man of God was.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As they went up the hill to the city, they met young women coming
        out to draw water and said to them, \u201CIs the seer here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They answered, \u201CHe is; behold, he is just ahead of you. Hurry.
        He has come just now to the city, because the people have a sacrifice today
        on the high place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As soon as you enter the city you will find him, before he goes up
        to the high place to eat. For the people will not eat till he comes, since
        he must bless the sacrifice; afterward those who are invited will eat. Now
        go up, for you will meet him immediately.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So they went up to the city. As they were entering the city, they
        saw Samuel coming out toward them on his way up to the high place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the day before Saul came, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        revealed to Samuel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTomorrow about this time I will send to you a man from the
        land of Benjamin, and you shall anoint him to be prince[[COMMENT(0)]] over
        my people Israel. He shall save my people from the hand of the Philistines.
        For I have seen my people, because their cry has come to me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:16 '
        content: 'Or Septuagint adds '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Samuel saw Saul, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told him, \u201CHere
        is the man of whom I spoke to you! He it is who shall restrain my people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Saul approached Samuel in the gate and said, \u201CTell me where
        is the house of the seer?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Samuel answered Saul, \u201CI am the seer. Go up before me to the
        high place, for today you shall eat with me, and in the morning I will let
        you go and will tell you all that is on your mind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As for your donkeys that were lost three days ago, do not set your
        mind on them, for they have been found. And for whom is all that is desirable
        in Israel? Is it not for you and for all your father\u2019s house?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul answered, \u201CAm I not a Benjaminite, from the least of the
        tribes of Israel? And is not my clan the humblest of all the clans of the
        tribe of Benjamin? Why then have you spoken to me in this way?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Samuel took Saul and his young man and brought them into the
        hall and gave them a place at the head of those who had been invited, who
        were about thirty persons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Samuel said to the cook, \u201CBring the portion I gave you,
        of which I said to you, \u2018Put it aside.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the cook took up the leg and what was on it and set them before
        Saul. And Samuel said, \u201CSee, what was kept is set before you. Eat, because
        it was kept for you until the hour appointed, that you might eat with the
        guests.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]So Saul ate with Samuel that day. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And when they came down from the high place into the city, a bed
        was spread for Saul on the roof, and he lay down to sleep.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:25 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then at the break of dawn[[COMMENT(0)]] Samuel called to Saul on
        the roof, \u201CUp, that I may send you on your way.\u201D So Saul arose,
        and both he and Samuel went out into the street.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "As they were going down to the outskirts of the city, Samuel said
        to Saul, \u201CTell the servant to pass on before us, and when he has passed
        on, stop here yourself for a while, that I may make known to you the word
        of God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Anointed King'
      title: Saul Anointed King
      number: 1
      content: "    Then Samuel took a flask of oil and poured it on his head and
        kissed him and said, \u201CHas not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> anointed
        you to be prince[[COMMENT(0)]] over his people Israel? And you shall reign
        over the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and you will save them
        from the hand of their surrounding enemies. And this shall be the sign to
        you that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has anointed you to be prince over
        his heritage. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: 'Or Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When you depart from me today, you will meet two men by Rachel\u2019s
        tomb in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah, and they will say to you, \u2018The
        donkeys that you went to seek are found, and now your father has ceased to
        care about the donkeys and is anxious about you, saying, \u201CWhat shall
        I do about my son?\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then you shall go on from there farther and come to the oak of Tabor.
        Three men going up to God at Bethel will meet you there, one carrying three
        young goats, another carrying three loaves of bread, and another carrying
        a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they will greet you and give you two loaves of bread, which you
        shall accept from their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'After that you shall come to Gibeath-elohim,[[COMMENT(0)]]  where
        there is a garrison of the Philistines. And there, as soon as you come to
        the city, you will meet a group of prophets coming down from the high place
        with harp, tambourine, flute, and lyre before them, prophesying. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rush upon
        you, and you will prophesy with them and be turned into another man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when these signs meet you, do what your hand finds to do, for
        God is with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then go down before me to Gilgal. And behold, I am coming down to
        you to offer burnt offerings and to sacrifice peace offerings. Seven days
        you shall wait, until I come to you and show you what you shall do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When he turned his back to leave Samuel, God gave him another heart.
        And all these signs came to pass that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to Gibeah,[[COMMENT(0)]] behold, a group of prophets
        met him, and the Spirit of God rushed upon him, and he prophesied among them. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when all who knew him previously saw how he prophesied with the
        prophets, the people said to one another, \u201CWhat has come over the son
        of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And a man of the place answered, \u201CAnd who is their father?\u201D
        Therefore it became a proverb, \u201CIs Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he had finished prophesying, he came to the high place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  Saul\u2019s uncle said to him and to his servant, \u201CWhere did
        you go?\u201D And he said, \u201CTo seek the donkeys. And when we saw they
        were not to be found, we went to Samuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Saul\u2019s uncle said, \u201CPlease tell me what Samuel said
        to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Saul Proclaimed King'
      title: Saul Proclaimed King
      number: 16
      content: "And Saul said to his uncle, \u201CHe told us plainly that the donkeys
        had been found.\u201D But about the matter of the kingdom, of which Samuel
        had spoken, he did not tell him anything.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now Samuel called the people together to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said to the people of Israel, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, \u2018I brought up Israel out of Egypt, and I delivered
        you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of all the kingdoms
        that were oppressing you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But today you have rejected your God, who saves you from all your
        calamities and your distresses, and you have said to him, \u2018Set a king
        over us.\u2019 Now therefore present yourselves before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by your tribes and by your thousands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Samuel brought all the tribes of Israel near, and the tribe
        of Benjamin was taken by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He brought the tribe of Benjamin near by its clans, and the clan
        of the Matrites was taken by lot;[[COMMENT(0)]] and Saul the son of Kish
        was taken by lot. But when they sought him, he could not be found. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:21 '
        content: 'Septuagint adds '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they inquired again of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CIs
        there a man still to come?\u201D and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said,
        \u201CBehold, he has hidden himself among the baggage.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then they ran and took him from there. And when he stood among the
        people, he was taller than any of the people from his shoulders upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Samuel said to all the people, \u201CDo you see him whom the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen? There is none like him among all
        the people.\u201D And all the people shouted, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Samuel told the people the rights and duties of the kingship,
        and he wrote them in a book and laid it up before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Then Samuel sent all the people away, each one to his home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Saul also went to his home at Gibeah, and with him went men of valor
        whose hearts God had touched. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But some worthless fellows said, \u201CHow can this man save us?\u201D
        And they despised him and brought him no present. But he held his peace."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Defeats the Ammonites'
      title: Saul Defeats the Ammonites
      number: 1
      content: "    Then Nahash the Ammonite went up and besieged Jabesh-gilead,
        and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201CMake a treaty with us, and
        we will serve you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Nahash the Ammonite said to them, \u201COn this condition I will
        make a treaty with you, that I gouge out all your right eyes, and thus bring
        disgrace on all Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The elders of Jabesh said to him, \u201CGive us seven days\u2019
        respite that we may send messengers through all the territory of Israel.
        Then, if there is no one to save us, we will give ourselves up to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul, they reported the matter
        in the ears of the people, and all the people wept aloud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now, behold, Saul was coming from the field behind the oxen. And
        Saul said, \u201CWhat is wrong with the people, that they are weeping?\u201D
        So they told him the news of the men of Jabesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Spirit of God rushed upon Saul when he heard these words,
        and his anger was greatly kindled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He took a yoke of oxen and cut them in pieces and sent them throughout
        all the territory of Israel by the hand of the messengers, saying, \u201CWhoever
        does not come out after Saul and Samuel, so shall it be done to his oxen!\u201D
        Then the dread of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> fell upon the people, and
        they came out as one man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When he mustered them at Bezek, the people of Israel were three hundred
        thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they said to the messengers who had come, \u201CThus shall you
        say to the men of Jabesh-gilead: \u2018Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot,
        you shall have salvation.\u2019\u201D When the messengers came and told the
        men of Jabesh, they were glad. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore the men of Jabesh said, \u201CTomorrow we will give ourselves
        up to you, and you may do to us whatever seems good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Kingdom Is Renewed'
      title: The Kingdom Is Renewed
      number: 11
      content: 'And the next day Saul put the people in three companies. And they
        came into the midst of the camp in the morning watch and struck down the
        Ammonites until the heat of the day. And those who survived were scattered,
        so that no two of them were left together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the people said to Samuel, \u201CWho is it that said, \u2018Shall
        Saul reign over us?\u2019 Bring the men, that we may put them to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Saul said, \u201CNot a man shall be put to death this day, for
        today the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has worked salvation in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CCome, let us go to Gilgal and
        there renew the kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So all the people went to Gilgal, and there they made Saul king before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Gilgal. There they sacrificed peace offerings
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and there Saul and all the men of
        Israel rejoiced greatly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s Farewell Address"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Farewell Address"
      number: 1
      content: "  And Samuel said to all Israel, \u201CBehold, I have obeyed your
        voice in all that you have said to me and have made a king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now, behold, the king walks before you, and I am old and gray;
        and behold, my sons are with you. I have walked before you from my youth
        until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Here I am; testify against me before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and before his anointed. Whose ox have I taken? Or whose donkey have I taken?
        Or whom have I defrauded? Whom have I oppressed? Or from whose hand have
        I taken a bribe to blind my eyes with it? Testify against me[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and I will restore it to you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They said, \u201CYou have not defrauded us or oppressed us or taken
        anything from any man\u2019s hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is witness
        against you, and his anointed is witness this day, that you have not found
        anything in my hand.\u201D And they said, \u201CHe is witness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Samuel said to the people, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is witness,[[COMMENT(0)]] who appointed Moses and Aaron and brought your
        fathers up out of the land of Egypt. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now therefore stand still that I may plead with you before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        concerning all the righteous deeds of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that
        he performed for you and for your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Jacob went into Egypt, and the Egyptians oppressed them,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        then your fathers cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent Moses and Aaron, who brought your fathers out of Egypt and made them
        dwell in this place. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:8 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they forgot the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. And he
        sold them into the hand of Sisera, commander of the army of Hazor,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and into the hand of the Philistines, and into the hand of the king of Moab.
        And they fought against them. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u2018We
        have sinned, because we have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and
        have served the Baals and the Ashtaroth. But now deliver us out of the hand
        of our enemies, that we may serve you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent Jerubbaal and Barak[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and Jephthah and Samuel and delivered you out of the hand of your enemies
        on every side, and you lived in safety. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:11 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And when you saw that Nahash the king of the Ammonites came against
        you, you said to me, \u2018No, but a king shall reign over us,\u2019 when
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God was your king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now behold the king whom you have chosen, for whom you have asked;
        behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has set a king over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you will fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and serve him and
        obey his voice and not rebel against the commandment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and if both you and the king who reigns over you will follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, it will be well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But if you will not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but rebel against the commandment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, then
        the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be against you and your
        king.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now therefore stand still and see this great thing that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will do before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Is it not wheat harvest today? I will call upon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that he may send thunder and rain. And you shall know and see that your wickedness
        is great, which you have done in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in asking for yourselves a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Samuel called upon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent thunder and rain that day, and all the people greatly feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and Samuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And all the people said to Samuel, \u201CPray for your servants to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, that we may not die, for we have
        added to all our sins this evil, to ask for ourselves a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Samuel said to the people, \u201CDo not be afraid; you have done
        all this evil. Yet do not turn aside from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And do not turn aside after empty things that cannot profit or deliver,
        for they are empty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not forsake his people,
        for his great name\u2019s sake, because it has pleased the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to make you a people for himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Moreover, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by ceasing to pray for you, and I will instruct
        you in the good and the right way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Only fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and serve him faithfully
        with all your heart. For consider what great things he has done for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if you still do wickedly, you shall be swept away, both you and
        your king.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Fights the Philistines'
      title: Saul Fights the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: '  Saul lived for one year and then became king, and when he had reigned
        for two years over Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: "Hebrew ; some Greek manuscripts give Saul\u2019s age when he began
          to reign as thirty years"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Saul chose three thousand men of Israel. Two thousand were with Saul
        in Michmash and the hill country of Bethel, and a thousand were with Jonathan
        in Gibeah of Benjamin. The rest of the people he sent home, every man to
        his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jonathan defeated the garrison of the Philistines that was at Geba,
        and the Philistines heard of it. And Saul blew the trumpet throughout all
        the land, saying, \u201CLet the Hebrews hear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And all Israel heard it said that Saul had defeated the garrison
        of the Philistines, and also that Israel had become a stench to the Philistines.
        And the people were called out to join Saul at Gilgal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Philistines mustered to fight with Israel, thirty thousand
        chariots and six thousand horsemen and troops like the sand on the seashore
        in multitude. They came up and encamped in Michmash, to the east of Beth-aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the men of Israel saw that they were in trouble (for the people
        were hard pressed), the people hid themselves in caves and in holes and in
        rocks and in tombs and in cisterns, '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Saul\u2019s Unlawful Sacrifice"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Unlawful Sacrifice"
      number: 7
      content: 'and some Hebrews crossed the fords of the Jordan to the land of Gad
        and Gilead. Saul was still at Gilgal, and all the people followed him trembling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  He waited seven days, the time appointed by Samuel. But Samuel
        did not come to Gilgal, and the people were scattering from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CBring the burnt offering here to me, and the
        peace offerings.\u201D And he offered the burnt offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As soon as he had finished offering the burnt offering, behold, Samuel
        came. And Saul went out to meet him and greet him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CWhat have you done?\u201D And Saul said, \u201CWhen
        I saw that the people were scattering from me, and that you did not come
        within the days appointed, and that the Philistines had mustered at Michmash, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I said, \u2018Now the Philistines will come down against me at Gilgal,
        and I have not sought the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019
        So I forced myself, and offered the burnt offering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Samuel said to Saul, \u201CYou have done foolishly. You have
        not kept the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, with which
        he commanded you. For then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> would have established
        your kingdom over Israel forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now your kingdom shall not continue. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sought out a man after his own heart, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has commanded him to be prince[[COMMENT(0)]] over his people, because you
        have not kept what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '13:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Samuel arose and went up from Gilgal. The rest of the people
        went up after Saul to meet the army; they went up from Gilgal[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to Gibeah of Benjamin.And Saul numbered the people who were present with
        him, about six hundred men. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Saul and Jonathan his son and the people who were present with
        them stayed in Geba of Benjamin, but the Philistines encamped in Michmash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And raiders came out of the camp of the Philistines in three companies.
        One company turned toward Ophrah, to the land of Shual; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'another company turned toward Beth-horon; and another company turned
        toward the border that looks down on the Valley of Zeboim toward the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  Now there was no blacksmith to be found throughout all the land
        of Israel, for the Philistines said, \u201CLest the Hebrews make themselves
        swords or spears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But every one of the Israelites went down to the Philistines to sharpen
        his plowshare, his mattock, his axe, or his sickle,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:20 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and the charge was two-thirds of a shekel[[COMMENT(0)]] for the plowshares
        and for the mattocks, and a third of a shekel for sharpening the axes and
        for setting the goads.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: Hebrew A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 gramsThe meaning of the Hebrew
          verse is uncertain
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So on the day of the battle there was neither sword nor spear found
        in the hand of any of the people with Saul and Jonathan, but Saul and Jonathan
        his son had them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And the garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass of Michmash.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Defeats the Philistines'
      title: Jonathan Defeats the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "  One day Jonathan the son of Saul said to the young man who carried
        his armor, \u201CCome, let us go over to the Philistine garrison on the other
        side.\u201D But he did not tell his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Saul was staying in the outskirts of Gibeah in the pomegranate cave[[COMMENT(0)]]
        at Migron. The people who were with him were about six hundred men, '
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: Or [tree]
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "including Ahijah the son of Ahitub, Ichabod\u2019s brother, son of
        Phinehas, son of Eli, the priest of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  in Shiloh,
        wearing an ephod. And the people did not know that Jonathan had gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Within the passes, by which Jonathan sought to go over to the Philistine
        garrison, there was a rocky crag on the one side and a rocky crag on the
        other side. The name of the one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The one crag rose on the north in front of Michmash, and the other
        on the south in front of Geba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jonathan said to the young man who carried his armor, \u201CCome,
        let us go over to the garrison of these uncircumcised. It may be that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will work for us, for nothing can hinder the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from saving by many or by few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And his armor-bearer said to him, \u201CDo all that is in your heart.
        Do as you wish.[[COMMENT(0)]] Behold, I am with you heart and soul.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CBehold, we will cross over to the men,
        and we will show ourselves to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If they say to us, \u2018Wait until we come to you,\u2019 then we
        will stand still in our place, and we will not go up to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But if they say, \u2018Come up to us,\u2019 then we will go up, for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given them into our hand. And this shall
        be the sign to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So both of them showed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines.
        And the Philistines said, \u201CLook, Hebrews are coming out of the holes
        where they have hidden themselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the men of the garrison hailed Jonathan and his armor-bearer
        and said, \u201CCome up to us, and we will show you a thing.\u201D And Jonathan
        said to his armor-bearer, \u201CCome up after me, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given them into the hand of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jonathan climbed up on his hands and feet, and his armor-bearer
        after him. And they fell before Jonathan, and his armor-bearer killed them
        after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And that first strike, which Jonathan and his armor-bearer made,
        killed about twenty men within as it were half a furrow\u2019s length in
        an acre[[COMMENT(0)]] of land. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And there was a panic in the camp, in the field, and among all the
        people. The garrison and even the raiders trembled, the earth quaked, and
        it became a very great panic.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the watchmen of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin looked, and behold,
        the multitude was dispersing here and there.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to the people who were with him, \u201CCount and see
        who has gone from us.\u201D And when they had counted, behold, Jonathan and
        his armor-bearer were not there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Saul said to Ahijah, \u201CBring the ark of God here.\u201D For
        the ark of God went at that time with the people[[COMMENT(0)]] of Israel. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now while Saul was talking to the priest, the tumult in the camp
        of the Philistines increased more and more. So Saul said to the priest, \u201CWithdraw
        your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul and all the people who were with him rallied and went into
        the battle. And behold, every Philistine\u2019s sword was against his fellow,
        and there was very great confusion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the Hebrews who had been with the Philistines before that time
        and who had gone up with them into the camp, even they also turned to be
        with the Israelites who were with Saul and Jonathan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Likewise, when all the men of Israel who had hidden themselves in
        the hill country of Ephraim heard that the Philistines were fleeing, they
        too followed hard after them in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Saul\u2019s Rash Vow"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Rash Vow"
      number: 23
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saved Israel that day. And the
        battle passed beyond Beth-aven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the men of Israel had been hard pressed that day, so Saul had
        laid an oath on the people, saying, \u201CCursed be the man who eats food
        until it is evening and I am avenged on my enemies.\u201D So none of the
        people had tasted food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now when all the people[[COMMENT(0)]] came to the forest, behold,
        there was honey on the ground. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when the people entered the forest, behold, the honey was dropping,
        but no one put his hand to his mouth, for the people feared the oath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Jonathan had not heard his father charge the people with the
        oath, so he put out the tip of the staff that was in his hand and dipped
        it in the honeycomb and put his hand to his mouth, and his eyes became bright. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then one of the people said, \u201CYour father strictly charged the
        people with an oath, saying, \u2018Cursed be the man who eats food this day.\u2019\u201D
        And the people were faint. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CMy father has troubled the land. See how
        my eyes have become bright because I tasted a little of this honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "How much better if the people had eaten freely today of the spoil
        of their enemies that they found. For now the defeat among the Philistines
        has not been great.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They struck down the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon.
        And the people were very faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The people pounced on the spoil and took sheep and oxen and calves
        and slaughtered them on the ground. And the people ate them with the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then they told Saul, \u201CBehold, the people are sinning against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by eating with the blood.\u201D And he said,
        \u201CYou have dealt treacherously; roll a great stone to me here.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:33 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CDisperse yourselves among the people and say
        to them, \u2018Let every man bring his ox or his sheep and slaughter them
        here and eat, and do not sin against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by eating
        with the blood.\u2019\u201D So every one of the people brought his ox with
        him that night and they slaughtered them there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Saul built an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; it was
        the first altar that he built to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CLet us go down after the Philistines by night
        and plunder them until the morning light; let us not leave a man of them.\u201D
        And they said, \u201CDo whatever seems good to you.\u201D But the priest
        said, \u201CLet us draw near to God here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And Saul inquired of God, \u201CShall I go down after the Philistines?
        Will you give them into the hand of Israel?\u201D But he did not answer him
        that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CCome here, all you leaders of the people, and
        know and see how this sin has arisen today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives who saves Israel, though
        it be in Jonathan my son, he shall surely die.\u201D But there was not a
        man among all the people who answered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he said to all Israel, \u201CYou shall be on one side, and I
        and Jonathan my son will be on the other side.\u201D And the people said
        to Saul, \u201CDo what seems good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Therefore Saul said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel,
        why have you not answered your servant this day? If this guilt is in me or
        in Jonathan my son, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Israel, give Urim.
        But if this guilt is in your people Israel, give Thummim.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        And Jonathan and Saul were taken, but the people escaped. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:41 '
        content: Vulgate and Septuagint; Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CCast the lot between me and my son Jonathan.\u201D
        And Jonathan was taken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then Saul said to Jonathan, \u201CTell me what you have done.\u201D
        And Jonathan told him, \u201CI tasted a little honey with the tip of the
        staff that was in my hand. Here I am; I will die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CGod do so to me and more also; you shall surely
        die, Jonathan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then the people said to Saul, \u201CShall Jonathan die, who has worked
        this great salvation in Israel? Far from it! As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, there shall not one hair of his head fall to the ground, for he has
        worked with God this day.\u201D So the people ransomed Jonathan, so that
        he did not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: "46: Saul Fights Israel\u2019s Enemies"
      title: "Saul Fights Israel\u2019s Enemies"
      number: 46
      content: 'Then Saul went up from pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines
        went to their own place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When Saul had taken the kingship over Israel, he fought against all
        his enemies on every side, against Moab, against the Ammonites, against Edom,
        against the kings of Zobah, and against the Philistines. Wherever he turned
        he routed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And he did valiantly and struck the Amalekites and delivered Israel
        out of the hands of those who plundered them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '  Now the sons of Saul were Jonathan, Ishvi, and Malchi-shua. And
        the names of his two daughters were these: the name of the firstborn was
        Merab, and the name of the younger Michal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "And the name of Saul\u2019s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz.
        And the name of the commander of his army was Abner the son of Ner, Saul\u2019s
        uncle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner was the
        son of Abiel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: There was hard fighting against the Philistines all the days of Saul.
        And when Saul saw any strong man, or any valiant man, he attached him to
        himself.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Rejects Saul'
      title: The  Rejects Saul
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  And Samuel said to Saul, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent me to anoint you king over his people Israel; now therefore listen to
        the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, \u2018I have
        noted what Amalek did to Israel in opposing them on the way when they came
        up out of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now go and strike Amalek and devote to destruction[[COMMENT(0)]]
        all that they have. Do not spare them, but kill both man and woman, child
        and infant, ox and sheep, camel and donkey.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:3 '
        content: That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          also verses 8, 9, 15, 18, 20, 21
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Saul summoned the people and numbered them in Telaim, two hundred
        thousand men on foot, and ten thousand men of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Saul came to the city of Amalek and lay in wait in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Saul said to the Kenites, \u201CGo, depart; go down from among
        the Amalekites, lest I destroy you with them. For you showed kindness to
        all the people of Israel when they came up out of Egypt.\u201D So the Kenites
        departed from among the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Saul defeated the Amalekites from Havilah as far as Shur, which
        is east of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he took Agag the king of the Amalekites alive and devoted to
        destruction all the people with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Saul and the people spared Agag and the best of the sheep and
        of the oxen and of the fattened calves[[COMMENT(0)]] and the lambs, and all
        that was good, and would not utterly destroy them. All that was despised
        and worthless they devoted to destruction.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:9 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew term is uncertain
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Samuel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI regret[[COMMENT(0)]] that I have made Saul king, for he has
        turned back from following me and has not performed my commandments.\u201D
        And Samuel was angry, and he cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all
        night. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:11 '
        content: See also verses 29, 35
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Samuel rose early to meet Saul in the morning. And it was told
        Samuel, \u201CSaul came to Carmel, and behold, he set up a monument for himself
        and turned and passed on and went down to Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Samuel came to Saul, and Saul said to him, \u201CBlessed be you
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I have performed the commandment of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CWhat then is this bleating of the sheep in
        my ears and the lowing of the oxen that I hear?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Saul said, \u201CThey have brought them from the Amalekites, for
        the people spared the best of the sheep and of the oxen to sacrifice to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and the rest we have devoted to destruction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CStop! I will tell you what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me this night.\u201D And he said to him, \u201CSpeak.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CThough you are little in your own eyes, are
        you not the head of the tribes of Israel? The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        anointed you king over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent you on a mission and said,
        \u2018Go, devote to destruction the sinners, the Amalekites, and fight against
        them until they are consumed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why then did you not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?
        Why did you pounce on the spoil and do what was evil in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have obeyed the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        I have gone on the mission on which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent
        me. I have brought Agag the king of Amalek, and I have devoted the Amalekites
        to destruction. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But the people took of the spoil, sheep and oxen, the best of the
        things devoted to destruction, to sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God in Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Samuel said,  \u201CHas the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as great
        delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices,as in obeying the voice of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Behold, to obey is better than sacrifice,and
        to listen than the fat of rams.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For rebellion is as the sin of divination,and presumption is as iniquity
        and idolatry.Because you have rejected the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        he has also rejected you from being king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have sinned, for I have transgressed
        the commandment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and your words, because
        I feared the people and obeyed their voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now therefore, please pardon my sin and return with me that I may
        bow before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Samuel said to Saul, \u201CI will not return with you. For you
        have rejected the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has rejected you from being king over Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As Samuel turned to go away, Saul seized the skirt of his robe, and
        it tore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Samuel said to him, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        torn the kingdom of Israel from you this day and has given it to a neighbor
        of yours, who is better than you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And also the Glory of Israel will not lie or have regret, for he
        is not a man, that he should have regret.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have sinned; yet honor me now before the elders
        of my people and before Israel, and return with me, that I may bow before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So Samuel turned back after Saul, and Saul bowed before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CBring here to me Agag the king of the Amalekites.\u201D
        And Agag came to him cheerfully.[[COMMENT(0)]] Agag said, \u201CSurely the
        bitterness of death is past.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:32 '
        content: Or (compare Septuagint); the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CAs your sword has made women childless, so
        shall your mother be childless among women.\u201D And Samuel hacked Agag
        to pieces before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  in Gilgal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Samuel went to Ramah, and Saul went up to his house in Gibeah
        of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And Samuel did not see Saul again until the day of his death, but
        Samuel grieved over Saul. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> regretted that
        he had made Saul king over Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King'
      title: David Anointed King
      number: 1
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Samuel, \u201CHow long
        will you grieve over Saul, since I have rejected him from being king over
        Israel? Fill your horn with oil, and go. I will send you to Jesse the Bethlehemite,
        for I have provided for myself a king among his sons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CHow can I go? If Saul hears it, he will kill
        me.\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CTake a heifer with
        you and say, \u2018I have come to sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show you what you shall
        do. And you shall anoint for me him whom I declare to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Samuel did what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded and came
        to Bethlehem. The elders of the city came to meet him trembling and said,
        \u201CDo you come peaceably?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, \u201CPeaceably; I have come to sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Consecrate yourselves, and come with me to the sacrifice.\u201D And he consecrated
        Jesse and his sons and invited them to the sacrifice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When they came, he looked on Eliab and thought, \u201CSurely the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed is before him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Samuel, \u201CDo not
        look on his appearance or on the height of his stature, because I have rejected
        him. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sees not as man sees: man looks
        on the outward appearance, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looks on the
        heart.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jesse called Abinadab and made him pass before Samuel. And he
        said, \u201CNeither has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chosen this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jesse made Shammah pass by. And he said, \u201CNeither has the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chosen this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jesse made seven of his sons pass before Samuel. And Samuel said
        to Jesse, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not chosen these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CAre all your sons here?\u201D And
        he said, \u201CThere remains yet the youngest,[[COMMENT(0)]] but behold,
        he is keeping the sheep.\u201D And Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CSend and get
        him, for we will not sit down till he comes here.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '16:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he sent and brought him in. Now he was ruddy and had beautiful
        eyes and was handsome. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CArise,
        anoint him, for this is he.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: David in Saul\u2019s Service"
      title: "David in Saul\u2019s Service"
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed him in the midst of
        his brothers. And the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rushed upon
        David from that day forward. And Samuel rose up and went to Ramah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Now the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> departed from
        Saul, and a harmful spirit from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> tormented
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Saul\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CBehold now, a harmful
        spirit from God is tormenting you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let our lord now command your servants who are before you to seek
        out a man who is skillful in playing the lyre, and when the harmful spirit
        from God is upon you, he will play it, and you will be well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Saul said to his servants, \u201CProvide for me a man who can
        play well and bring him to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One of the young men answered, \u201CBehold, I have seen a son of
        Jesse the Bethlehemite, who is skillful in playing, a man of valor, a man
        of war, prudent in speech, and a man of good presence, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore Saul sent messengers to Jesse and said, \u201CSend me David
        your son, who is with the sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jesse took a donkey laden with bread and a skin of wine and a
        young goat and sent them by David his son to Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And David came to Saul and entered his service. And Saul loved him
        greatly, and he became his armor-bearer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Saul sent to Jesse, saying, \u201CLet David remain in my service,
        for he has found favor in my sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And whenever the harmful spirit from God was upon Saul, David took
        the lyre and played it with his hand. So Saul was refreshed and was well,
        and the harmful spirit departed from him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and Goliath'
      title: David and Goliath
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines gathered their armies for battle. And they
        were gathered at Socoh, which belongs to Judah, and encamped between Socoh
        and Azekah, in Ephes-dammim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Saul and the men of Israel were gathered, and encamped in the
        Valley of Elah, and drew up in line of battle against the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the Philistines stood on the mountain on the one side, and Israel
        stood on the mountain on the other side, with a valley between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And there came out from the camp of the Philistines a champion named
        Goliath of Gath, whose height was six[[COMMENT(0)]] cubits and a span. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:4 '
        content: Hebrew; Septuagint, Dead Sea Scroll and Josephus A was about 18
          inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He had a helmet of bronze on his head, and he was armed with a coat
        of mail, and the weight of the coat was five thousand shekels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of bronze. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:5 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he had bronze armor on his legs, and a javelin of bronze slung
        between his shoulders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The shaft of his spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam, and his spear\u2019s
        head weighed six hundred shekels of iron. And his shield-bearer went before
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He stood and shouted to the ranks of Israel, \u201CWhy have you come
        out to draw up for battle? Am I not a Philistine, and are you not servants
        of Saul? Choose a man for yourselves, and let him come down to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then we will be your
        servants. But if I prevail against him and kill him, then you shall be our
        servants and serve us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the Philistine said, \u201CI defy the ranks of Israel this day.
        Give me a man, that we may fight together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they
        were dismayed and greatly afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now David was the son of an Ephrathite of Bethlehem in Judah, named
        Jesse, who had eight sons. In the days of Saul the man was already old and
        advanced in years.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:12 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The three oldest sons of Jesse had followed Saul to the battle. And
        the names of his three sons who went to the battle were Eliab the firstborn,
        and next to him Abinadab, and the third Shammah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was the youngest. The three eldest followed Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but David went back and forth from Saul to feed his father\u2019s
        sheep at Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For forty days the Philistine came forward and took his stand, morning
        and evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Jesse said to David his son, \u201CTake for your brothers an
        ephah[[COMMENT(0)]] of this parched grain, and these ten loaves, and carry
        them quickly to the camp to your brothers. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:17 '
        content: An was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Also take these ten cheeses to the commander of their thousand. See
        if your brothers are well, and bring some token from them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now Saul and they and all the men of Israel were in the Valley of
        Elah, fighting with the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And David rose early in the morning and left the sheep with a keeper
        and took the provisions and went, as Jesse had commanded him. And he came
        to the encampment as the host was going out to the battle line, shouting
        the war cry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Israel and the Philistines drew up for battle, army against army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And David left the things in charge of the keeper of the baggage
        and ran to the ranks and went and greeted his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As he talked with them, behold, the champion, the Philistine of Gath,
        Goliath by name, came up out of the ranks of the Philistines and spoke the
        same words as before. And David heard him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the men of Israel, when they saw the man, fled from him and were
        much afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And the men of Israel said, \u201CHave you seen this man who has
        come up? Surely he has come up to defy Israel. And the king will enrich the
        man who kills him with great riches and will give him his daughter and make
        his father\u2019s house free in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And David said to the men who stood by him, \u201CWhat shall be done
        for the man who kills this Philistine and takes away the reproach from Israel?
        For who is this uncircumcised Philistine, that he should defy the armies
        of the living God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the people answered him in the same way, \u201CSo shall it be
        done to the man who kills him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now Eliab his eldest brother heard when he spoke to the men. And
        Eliab\u2019s anger was kindled against David, and he said, \u201CWhy have
        you come down? And with whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness?
        I know your presumption and the evil of your heart, for you have come down
        to see the battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And David said, \u201CWhat have I done now? Was it not but a word?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And he turned away from him toward another, and spoke in the same
        way, and the people answered him again as before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When the words that David spoke were heard, they repeated them before
        Saul, and he sent for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And David said to Saul, \u201CLet no man\u2019s heart fail because
        of him. Your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And Saul said to David, \u201CYou are not able to go against this
        Philistine to fight with him, for you are but a youth, and he has been a
        man of war from his youth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But David said to Saul, \u201CYour servant used to keep sheep for
        his father. And when there came a lion, or a bear, and took a lamb from the
        flock, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I went after him and struck him and delivered it out of his mouth.
        And if he arose against me, I caught him by his beard and struck him and
        killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Your servant has struck down both lions and bears, and this uncircumcised
        Philistine shall be like one of them, for he has defied the armies of the
        living God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And David said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who delivered
        me from the paw of the lion and from the paw of the bear will deliver me
        from the hand of this Philistine.\u201D And Saul said to David, \u201CGo,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Saul clothed David with his armor. He put a helmet of bronze
        on his head and clothed him with a coat of mail, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "and David strapped his sword over his armor. And he tried in vain
        to go, for he had not tested them. Then David said to Saul, \u201CI cannot
        go with these, for I have not tested them.\u201D So David put them off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he took his staff in his hand and chose five smooth stones from
        the brook and put them in his shepherd\u2019s pouch. His sling was in his
        hand, and he approached the Philistine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the Philistine moved forward and came near to David, with his
        shield-bearer in front of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And when the Philistine looked and saw David, he disdained him, for
        he was but a youth, ruddy and handsome in appearance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And the Philistine said to David, \u201CAm I a dog, that you come
        to me with sticks?\u201D And the Philistine cursed David by his gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The Philistine said to David, \u201CCome to me, and I will give your
        flesh to the birds of the air and to the beasts of the field.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then David said to the Philistine, \u201CYou come to me with a sword
        and with a spear and with a javelin, but I come to you in the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of the armies of Israel, whom
        you have defied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'This day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will deliver you into my
        hand, and I will strike you down and cut off your head. And I will give the
        dead bodies of the host of the Philistines this day to the birds of the air
        and to the wild beasts of the earth, that all the earth may know that there
        is a God in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "and that all this assembly may know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        saves not with sword and spear. For the battle is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,
        and he will give you into our hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When the Philistine arose and came and drew near to meet David, David
        ran quickly toward the battle line to meet the Philistine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And David put his hand in his bag and took out a stone and slung
        it and struck the Philistine on his forehead. The stone sank into his forehead,
        and he fell on his face to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'So David prevailed over the Philistine with a sling and with a stone,
        and struck the Philistine and killed him. There was no sword in the hand
        of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Then David ran and stood over the Philistine and took his sword and
        drew it out of its sheath and killed him and cut off his head with it. When
        the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And the men of Israel and Judah rose with a shout and pursued the
        Philistines as far as Gath[[COMMENT(0)]] and the gates of Ekron, so that
        the wounded Philistines fell on the way from Shaaraim as far as Gath and
        Ekron. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:52 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the people of Israel came back from chasing the Philistines,
        and they plundered their camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem,
        but he put his armor in his tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "As soon as Saul saw David go out against the Philistine, he said
        to Abner, the commander of the army, \u201CAbner, whose son is this youth?\u201D
        And Abner said, \u201CAs your soul lives, O king, I do not know.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "And the king said, \u201CInquire whose son the boy is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'And as soon as David returned from the striking down of the Philistine,
        Abner took him, and brought him before Saul with the head of the Philistine
        in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "And Saul said to him, \u201CWhose son are you, young man?\u201D And
        David answered, \u201CI am the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David and Jonathan\u2019s Friendship"
      title: "David and Jonathan\u2019s Friendship"
      number: 1
      content: '  As soon as he had finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan
        was knit to the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Saul took him that day and would not let him return to his father\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jonathan made a covenant with David, because he loved him as
        his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Jonathan stripped himself of the robe that was on him and gave
        it to David, and his armor, and even his sword and his bow and his belt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Saul\u2019s Jealousy of David"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Jealousy of David"
      number: 5
      content: "And David went out and was successful wherever Saul sent him, so
        that Saul set him over the men of war. And this was good in the sight of
        all the people and also in the sight of Saul\u2019s servants.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As they were coming home, when David returned from striking down
        the Philistine, the women came out of all the cities of Israel, singing and
        dancing, to meet King Saul, with tambourines, with songs of joy, and with
        musical instruments.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:6 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the women sang to one another as they celebrated,  \u201CSaul
        has struck down his thousands,and David his ten thousands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Saul was very angry, and this saying displeased him. He said,
        \u201CThey have ascribed to David ten thousands, and to me they have ascribed
        thousands, and what more can he have but the kingdom?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Saul eyed David from that day on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The next day a harmful spirit from God rushed upon Saul, and he raved
        within his house while David was playing the lyre, as he did day by day.
        Saul had his spear in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Saul hurled the spear, for he thought, \u201CI will pin David
        to the wall.\u201D But David evaded him twice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Saul was afraid of David because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was with him but had departed from Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul removed him from his presence and made him a commander of
        a thousand. And he went out and came in before the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And David had success in all his undertakings, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when Saul saw that he had great success, he stood in fearful
        awe of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: David Marries Michal'
      title: David Marries Michal
      number: 16
      content: 'But all Israel and Judah loved David, for he went out and came in
        before them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CHere is my elder daughter Merab. I
        will give her to you for a wife. Only be valiant for me and fight the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        battles.\u201D For Saul thought, \u201CLet not my hand be against him, but
        let the hand of the Philistines be against him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And David said to Saul, \u201CWho am I, and who are my relatives,
        my father\u2019s clan in Israel, that I should be son-in-law to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But at the time when Merab, Saul\u2019s daughter, should have been
        given to David, she was given to Adriel the Meholathite for a wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s daughter Michal loved David. And they told Saul,
        and the thing pleased him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul thought, \u201CLet me give her to him, that she may be a snare
        for him and that the hand of the Philistines may be against him.\u201D Therefore
        Saul said to David a second time,[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CYou shall now be my
        son-in-law.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Saul commanded his servants, \u201CSpeak to David in private
        and say, \u2018Behold, the king has delight in you, and all his servants
        love you. Now then become the king\u2019s son-in-law.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Saul\u2019s servants spoke those words in the ears of David.
        And David said, \u201CDoes it seem to you a little thing to become the king\u2019s
        son-in-law, since I am a poor man and have no reputation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the servants of Saul told him, \u201CThus and so did David speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CThus shall you say to David, \u2018The king
        desires no bride-price except a hundred foreskins of the Philistines, that
        he may be avenged of the king\u2019s enemies.\u2019\u201D Now Saul thought
        to make David fall by the hand of the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And when his servants told David these words, it pleased David well
        to be the king\u2019s son-in-law. Before the time had expired, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "David arose and went, along with his men, and killed two hundred
        of the Philistines. And David brought their foreskins, which were given in
        full number to the king, that he might become the king\u2019s son-in-law.
        And Saul gave him his daughter Michal for a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But when Saul saw and knew that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was
        with David, and that Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, loved him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Saul was even more afraid of David. So Saul was David\u2019s enemy
        continually.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Then the commanders of the Philistines came out to battle, and
        as often as they came out David had more success than all the servants of
        Saul, so that his name was highly esteemed.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Tries to Kill David'
      title: Saul Tries to Kill David
      number: 1
      content: "  And Saul spoke to Jonathan his son and to all his servants, that
        they should kill David. But Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, delighted much in
        David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jonathan told David, \u201CSaul my father seeks to kill you.
        Therefore be on your guard in the morning. Stay in a secret place and hide
        yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I will go out and stand beside my father in the field where you
        are, and I will speak to my father about you. And if I learn anything I will
        tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jonathan spoke well of David to Saul his father and said to him,
        \u201CLet not the king sin against his servant David, because he has not
        sinned against you, and because his deeds have brought good to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For he took his life in his hand and he struck down the Philistine,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> worked a great salvation for all Israel.
        You saw it, and rejoiced. Why then will you sin against innocent blood by
        killing David without cause?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Saul listened to the voice of Jonathan. Saul swore, \u201CAs
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, he shall not be put to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Jonathan called David, and Jonathan reported to him all these
        things. And Jonathan brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence as
        before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And there was war again. And David went out and fought with the Philistines
        and struck them with a great blow, so that they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then a harmful spirit from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came upon
        Saul, as he sat in his house with his spear in his hand. And David was playing
        the lyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Saul sought to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he eluded
        Saul, so that he struck the spear into the wall. And David fled and escaped
        that night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  Saul sent messengers to David\u2019s house to watch him, that he
        might kill him in the morning. But Michal, David\u2019s wife, told him, \u201CIf
        you do not escape with your life tonight, tomorrow you will be killed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Michal let David down through the window, and he fled away and
        escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Michal took an image[[COMMENT(0)]] and laid it on the bed and put
        a pillow of goats\u2019 hair at its head and covered it with the clothes. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, \u201CHe is
        sick.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Saul sent the messengers to see David, saying, \u201CBring him
        up to me in the bed, that I may kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when the messengers came in, behold, the image was in the bed,
        with the pillow of goats\u2019 hair at its head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Saul said to Michal, \u201CWhy have you deceived me thus and let
        my enemy go, so that he has escaped?\u201D And Michal answered Saul, \u201CHe
        said to me, \u2018Let me go. Why should I kill you?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now David fled and escaped, and he came to Samuel at Ramah and told
        him all that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and lived at Naioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And it was told Saul, \u201CBehold, David is at Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Saul sent messengers to take David, and when they saw the company
        of the prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing as head over them, the Spirit
        of God came upon the messengers of Saul, and they also prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When it was told Saul, he sent other messengers, and they also prophesied.
        And Saul sent messengers again the third time, and they also prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he himself went to Ramah and came to the great well that is
        in Secu. And he asked, \u201CWhere are Samuel and David?\u201D And one said,
        \u201CBehold, they are at Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he went there to Naioth in Ramah. And the Spirit of God came
        upon him also, and as he went he prophesied until he came to Naioth in Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he too stripped off his clothes, and he too prophesied before
        Samuel and lay naked all that day and all that night. Thus it is said, \u201CIs
        Saul also among the prophets?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Warns David'
      title: Jonathan Warns David
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David fled from Naioth in Ramah and came and said before Jonathan,
        \u201CWhat have I done? What is my guilt? And what is my sin before your
        father, that he seeks my life?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CFar from it! You shall not die. Behold,
        my father does nothing either great or small without disclosing it to me.
        And why should my father hide this from me? It is not so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David vowed again, saying, \u201CYour father knows well that
        I have found favor in your eyes, and he thinks, \u2018Do not let Jonathan
        know this, lest he be grieved.\u2019 But truly, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives and as your soul lives, there is but a step between me and death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CWhatever you say, I will do for
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David said to Jonathan, \u201CBehold, tomorrow is the new moon, and
        I should not fail to sit at table with the king. But let me go, that I may
        hide myself in the field till the third day at evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If your father misses me at all, then say, \u2018David earnestly
        asked leave of me to run to Bethlehem his city, for there is a yearly sacrifice
        there for all the clan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If he says, \u2018Good!\u2019 it will be well with your servant,
        but if he is angry, then know that harm is determined by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore deal kindly with your servant, for you have brought your
        servant into a covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with you. But
        if there is guilt in me, kill me yourself, for why should you bring me to
        your father?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jonathan said, \u201CFar be it from you! If I knew that it was
        determined by my father that harm should come to you, would I not tell you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said to Jonathan, \u201CWho will tell me if your father
        answers you roughly?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Jonathan said to David, \u201CCome, let us go out into the field.\u201D
        So they both went out into the field.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Jonathan said to David, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, be witness![[COMMENT(0)]] When I have sounded out my father,
        about this time tomorrow, or the third day, behold, if he is well disposed
        toward David, shall I not then send and disclose it to you? "
      comments:
      - number: '20:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But should it please my father to do you harm, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        do so to Jonathan and more also if I do not disclose it to you and send you
        away, that you may go in safety. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with
        you, as he has been with my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If I am still alive, show me the steadfast love of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that I may not die; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and do not cut off[[COMMENT(0)]] your steadfast love from my house
        forever, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> cuts off every one of the enemies
        of David from the face of the earth.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '20:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David, saying, \u201CMay[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> take vengeance on David\u2019s enemies.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '20:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Jonathan made David swear again by his love for him, for he loved
        him as he loved his own soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jonathan said to him, \u201CTomorrow is the new moon, and you
        will be missed, because your seat will be empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'On the third day go down quickly to the place where you hid yourself
        when the matter was in hand, and remain beside the stone heap.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:19 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And I will shoot three arrows to the side of it, as though I shot
        at a mark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And behold, I will send the boy, saying, \u2018Go, find the arrows.\u2019
        If I say to the boy, \u2018Look, the arrows are on this side of you, take
        them,\u2019 then you are to come, for, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, it is safe for you and there is no danger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if I say to the youth, \u2018Look, the arrows are beyond you,\u2019
        then go, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent you away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And as for the matter of which you and I have spoken, behold, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is between you and me forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So David hid himself in the field. And when the new moon came, the
        king sat down to eat food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The king sat on his seat, as at other times, on the seat by the wall.
        Jonathan sat opposite,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Abner sat by Saul\u2019s side, but
        David\u2019s place was empty.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:25 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Yet Saul did not say anything that day, for he thought, \u201CSomething
        has happened to him. He is not clean; surely he is not clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But on the second day, the day after the new moon, David\u2019s place
        was empty. And Saul said to Jonathan his son, \u201CWhy has not the son of
        Jesse come to the meal, either yesterday or today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jonathan answered Saul, \u201CDavid earnestly asked leave of me to
        go to Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He said, \u2018Let me go, for our clan holds a sacrifice in the city,
        and my brother has commanded me to be there. So now, if I have found favor
        in your eyes, let me get away and see my brothers.\u2019 For this reason
        he has not come to the king\u2019s table.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Saul\u2019s anger was kindled against Jonathan, and he said
        to him, \u201CYou son of a perverse, rebellious woman, do I not know that
        you have chosen the son of Jesse to your own shame, and to the shame of your
        mother\u2019s nakedness? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, neither you nor
        your kingdom shall be established. Therefore send and bring him to me, for
        he shall surely die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jonathan answered Saul his father, \u201CWhy should he be put
        to death? What has he done?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But Saul hurled his spear at him to strike him. So Jonathan knew
        that his father was determined to put David to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Jonathan rose from the table in fierce anger and ate no food
        the second day of the month, for he was grieved for David, because his father
        had disgraced him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'In the morning Jonathan went out into the field to the appointment
        with David, and with him a little boy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he said to his boy, \u201CRun and find the arrows that I shoot.\u201D
        As the boy ran, he shot an arrow beyond him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And when the boy came to the place of the arrow that Jonathan had
        shot, Jonathan called after the boy and said, \u201CIs not the arrow beyond
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Jonathan called after the boy, \u201CHurry! Be quick! Do not
        stay!\u201D So Jonathan\u2019s boy gathered up the arrows and came to his
        master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But the boy knew nothing. Only Jonathan and David knew the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And Jonathan gave his weapons to his boy and said to him, \u201CGo
        and carry them to the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And as soon as the boy had gone, David rose from beside the stone
        heap[[COMMENT(0)]] and fell on his face to the ground and bowed three times.
        And they kissed one another and wept with one another, David weeping the
        most. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:41 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CGo in peace, because we have sworn
        both of us in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, saying, \u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be between me and you, and between my offspring
        and your offspring, forever.\u2019\u201D And he rose and departed, and Jonathan
        went into the city.[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '20:42 '
        content: This sentence is 21:1 in Hebrew
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and the Holy Bread'
      title: David and the Holy Bread
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]] Then David came to Nob, to Ahimelech the priest.
        And Ahimelech came to meet David, trembling, and said to him, \u201CWhy are
        you alone, and no one with you?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '21:1 '
        content: '  Ch 21:2 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said to Ahimelech the priest, \u201CThe king has charged
        me with a matter and said to me, \u2018Let no one know anything of the matter
        about which I send you, and with which I have charged you.\u2019 I have made
        an appointment with the young men for such and such a place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now then, what do you have on hand? Give me five loaves of bread,
        or whatever is here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the priest answered David, \u201CI have no common bread on hand,
        but there is holy bread\u2014if the young men have kept themselves from women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And David answered the priest, \u201CTruly women have been kept from
        us as always when I go on an expedition. The vessels of the young men are
        holy even when it is an ordinary journey. How much more today will their
        vessels be holy?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the priest gave him the holy bread, for there was no bread there
        but the bread of the Presence, which is removed from before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to be replaced by hot bread on the day it is taken away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now a certain man of the servants of Saul was there that day, detained
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. His name was Doeg the Edomite, the
        chief of Saul\u2019s herdsmen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to Ahimelech, \u201CThen have you not here a spear
        or a sword at hand? For I have brought neither my sword nor my weapons with
        me, because the king\u2019s business required haste.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: David Flees to Gath'
      title: David Flees to Gath
      number: 9
      content: "And the priest said, \u201CThe sword of Goliath the Philistine, whom
        you struck down in the Valley of Elah, behold, it is here wrapped in a cloth
        behind the ephod. If you will take that, take it, for there is none but that
        here.\u201D And David said, \u201CThere is none like that; give it to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And David rose and fled that day from Saul and went to Achish the
        king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the servants of Achish said to him, \u201CIs not this David the
        king of the land? Did they not sing to one another of him in dances,\u2018Saul
        has struck down his thousands,and David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And David took these words to heart and was much afraid of Achish
        the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he changed his behavior before them and pretended to be insane
        in their hands and made marks on the doors of the gate and let his spittle
        run down his beard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Achish said to his servants, \u201CBehold, you see the man is
        mad. Why then have you brought him to me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Do I lack madmen, that you have brought this fellow to behave as
        a madman in my presence? Shall this fellow come into my house?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David at the Cave of Adullam'
      title: David at the Cave of Adullam
      number: 1
      content: "  David departed from there and escaped to the cave of Adullam. And
        when his brothers and all his father\u2019s house heard it, they went down
        there to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And everyone who was in distress, and everyone who was in debt, and
        everyone who was bitter in soul,[[COMMENT(0)]] gathered to him. And he became
        commander over them. And there were with him about four hundred men.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David went from there to Mizpeh of Moab. And he said to the king
        of Moab, \u201CPlease let my father and my mother stay[[COMMENT(0)]] with
        you, till I know what God will do for me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '22:3 '
        content: 'Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he left them with the king of Moab, and they stayed with him
        all the time that David was in the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Saul Kills the Priests at Nob'
      title: Saul Kills the Priests at Nob
      number: 5
      content: "Then the prophet Gad said to David, \u201CDo not remain in the stronghold;
        depart, and go into the land of Judah.\u201D So David departed and went into
        the forest of Hereth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now Saul heard that David was discovered, and the men who were with
        him. Saul was sitting at Gibeah under the tamarisk tree on the height with
        his spear in his hand, and all his servants were standing about him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Saul said to his servants who stood about him, \u201CHear now,
        people of Benjamin; will the son of Jesse give every one of you fields and
        vineyards, will he make you all commanders of thousands and commanders of
        hundreds, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "that all of you have conspired against me? No one discloses to me
        when my son makes a covenant with the son of Jesse. None of you is sorry
        for me or discloses to me that my son has stirred up my servant against me,
        to lie in wait, as at this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then answered Doeg the Edomite, who stood by the servants of Saul,
        \u201CI saw the son of Jesse coming to Nob, to Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and he inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for him and gave
        him provisions and gave him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the king sent to summon Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub,
        and all his father\u2019s house, the priests who were at Nob, and all of
        them came to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CHear now, son of Ahitub.\u201D And he answered,
        \u201CHere I am, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Saul said to him, \u201CWhy have you conspired against me, you
        and the son of Jesse, in that you have given him bread and a sword and have
        inquired of God for him, so that he has risen against me, to lie in wait,
        as at this day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Ahimelech answered the king, \u201CAnd who among all your servants
        is so faithful as David, who is the king\u2019s son-in-law, and captain over[[COMMENT(0)]]
        your bodyguard, and honored in your house? "
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Targum; Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Is today the first time that I have inquired of God for him? No!
        Let not the king impute anything to his servant or to all the house of my
        father, for your servant has known nothing of all this, much or little.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the king said, \u201CYou shall surely die, Ahimelech, you and
        all your father\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the king said to the guard who stood about him, \u201CTurn and
        kill the priests of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, because their hand also
        is with David, and they knew that he fled and did not disclose it to me.\u201D
        But the servants of the king would not put out their hand to strike the priests
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king said to Doeg, \u201CYou turn and strike the priests.\u201D
        And Doeg the Edomite turned and struck down the priests, and he killed on
        that day eighty-five persons who wore the linen ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Nob, the city of the priests, he put to the sword; both man and
        woman, child and infant, ox, donkey and sheep, he put to the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar,
        escaped and fled after David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Abiathar told David that Saul had killed the priests of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David said to Abiathar, \u201CI knew on that day, when Doeg the
        Edomite was there, that he would surely tell Saul. I have occasioned the
        death of all the persons of your father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Stay with me; do not be afraid, for he who seeks my life seeks your
        life. With me you shall be in safekeeping.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Saves the City of Keilah'
      title: David Saves the City of Keilah
      number: 1
      content: "  Now they told David, \u201CBehold, the Philistines are fighting
        against Keilah and are robbing the threshing floors.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CShall
        I go and attack these Philistines?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to David, \u201CGo and attack the Philistines and save Keilah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CBehold, we are afraid here
        in Judah; how much more then if we go to Keilah against the armies of the
        Philistines?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> again. And
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered him, \u201CArise, go down to Keilah,
        for I will give the Philistines into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And David and his men went to Keilah and fought with the Philistines
        and brought away their livestock and struck them with a great blow. So David
        saved the inhabitants of Keilah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  When Abiathar the son of Ahimelech had fled to David to Keilah,
        he had come down with an ephod in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now it was told Saul that David had come to Keilah. And Saul said,
        \u201CGod has given him into my hand, for he has shut himself in by entering
        a town that has gates and bars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Saul summoned all the people to war, to go down to Keilah, to
        besiege David and his men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "David knew that Saul was plotting harm against him. And he said to
        Abiathar the priest, \u201CBring the ephod here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, your servant has surely heard that Saul seeks to come to Keilah,
        to destroy the city on my account. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Will the men of Keilah surrender me into his hand? Will Saul come
        down, as your servant has heard? O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, please tell your servant.\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said, \u201CHe will come down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said, \u201CWill the men of Keilah surrender me and my
        men into the hand of Saul?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said,
        \u201CThey will surrender you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David and his men, who were about six hundred, arose and departed
        from Keilah, and they went wherever they could go. When Saul was told that
        David had escaped from Keilah, he gave up the expedition. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Saul Pursues David'
      title: Saul Pursues David
      number: 14
      content: 'And David remained in the strongholds in the wilderness, in the hill
        country of the wilderness of Ziph. And Saul sought him every day, but God
        did not give him into his hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'David saw that Saul had come out to seek his life. David was in the
        wilderness of Ziph at Horesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, rose and went to David at Horesh,
        and strengthened his hand in God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CDo not fear, for the hand of Saul my father
        shall not find you. You shall be king over Israel, and I shall be next to
        you. Saul my father also knows this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the two of them made a covenant before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        David remained at Horesh, and Jonathan went home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  Then the Ziphites went up to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs not
        David hiding among us in the strongholds at Horesh, on the hill of Hachilah,
        which is south of Jeshimon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now come down, O king, according to all your heart\u2019s desire
        to come down, and our part shall be to surrender him into the king\u2019s
        hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CMay you be blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for you have had compassion on me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Go, make yet more sure. Know and see the place where his foot is,
        and who has seen him there, for it is told me that he is very cunning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "See therefore and take note of all the lurking places where he hides,
        and come back to me with sure information. Then I will go with you. And if
        he is in the land, I will search him out among all the thousands of Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they arose and went to Ziph ahead of Saul.Now David and his men
        were in the wilderness of Maon, in the Arabah to the south of Jeshimon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Saul and his men went to seek him. And David was told, so he
        went down to the rock and lived in the wilderness of Maon. And when Saul
        heard that, he pursued after David in the wilderness of Maon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men on the
        other side of the mountain. And David was hurrying to get away from Saul.
        As Saul and his men were closing in on David and his men to capture them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "a messenger came to Saul, saying, \u201CHurry and come, for the Philistines
        have made a raid against the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Saul returned from pursuing after David and went against the Philistines.
        Therefore that place was called the Rock of Escape.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:28 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]] And David went up from there and lived in the strongholds
        of Engedi.'
      comments:
      - number: '23:29 '
        content: Ch 24:1 in Hebrew
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David Spares Saul\u2019s Life"
      title: "David Spares Saul\u2019s Life"
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]  When Saul returned from following the Philistines,
        he was told, \u201CBehold, David is in the wilderness of Engedi.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '24:1 '
        content: '  Ch 24:2 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Saul took three thousand chosen men out of all Israel and went
        to seek David and his men in front of the Wildgoats\u2019 Rocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he came to the sheepfolds by the way, where there was a cave,
        and Saul went in to relieve himself.[[COMMENT(0)]] Now David and his men
        were sitting in the innermost parts of the cave. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the men of David said to him, \u201CHere is the day of which
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to you, \u2018Behold, I will give your
        enemy into your hand, and you shall do to him as it shall seem good to you.\u2019\u201D
        Then David arose and stealthily cut off a corner of Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And afterward David\u2019s heart struck him, because he had cut off
        a corner of Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to his men, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forbid
        that I should do this thing to my lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed, to put out my hand against him, seeing he is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David persuaded his men with these words and did not permit them
        to attack Saul. And Saul rose up and left the cave and went on his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Afterward David also arose and went out of the cave, and called after
        Saul, \u201CMy lord the king!\u201D And when Saul looked behind him, David
        bowed with his face to the earth and paid homage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And David said to Saul, \u201CWhy do you listen to the words of men
        who say, \u2018Behold, David seeks your harm\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Behold, this day your eyes have seen how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave you today into my hand in the cave. And some told me to kill you, but
        I spared you.[[COMMENT(0)]] I said, \u2018I will not put out my hand against
        my lord, for he is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '24:10 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Targum; Hebrew [my eye] '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'See, my father, see the corner of your robe in my hand. For by the
        fact that I cut off the corner of your robe and did not kill you, you may
        know and see that there is no wrong or treason in my hands. I have not sinned
        against you, though you hunt my life to take it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> judge between me and you, may
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> avenge me against you, but my hand shall
        not be against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As the proverb of the ancients says, \u2018Out of the wicked comes
        wickedness.\u2019 But my hand shall not be against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After whom has the king of Israel come out? After whom do you pursue?
        After a dead dog! After a flea! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> therefore be judge and give sentence
        between me and you, and see to it and plead my cause and deliver me from
        your hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "As soon as David had finished speaking these words to Saul, Saul
        said, \u201CIs this your voice, my son David?\u201D And Saul lifted up his
        voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said to David, \u201CYou are more righteous than I, for you have
        repaid me good, whereas I have repaid you evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you have declared this day how you have dealt well with me, in
        that you did not kill me when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> put me into
        your hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For if a man finds his enemy, will he let him go away safe? So may
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reward you with good for what you have done
        to me this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And now, behold, I know that you shall surely be king, and that the
        kingdom of Israel shall be established in your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Swear to me therefore by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that you
        will not cut off my offspring after me, and that you will not destroy my
        name out of my father\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And David swore this to Saul. Then Saul went home, but David and his
        men went up to the stronghold.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of SamuelDavid and Abigail'
      title: The Death of SamuelDavid and Abigail
      number: 1
      content: '    Now Samuel died. And all Israel assembled and mourned for him,
        and they buried him in his house at Ramah.Then David rose and went down to
        the wilderness of Paran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And there was a man in Maon whose business was in Carmel. The man
        was very rich; he had three thousand sheep and a thousand goats. He was shearing
        his sheep in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the name of the man was Nabal, and the name of his wife Abigail.
        The woman was discerning and beautiful, but the man was harsh and badly behaved;
        he was a Calebite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent ten young men. And David said to the young men, \u201CGo
        up to Carmel, and go to Nabal and greet him in my name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And thus you shall greet him: \u2018Peace be to you, and peace be
        to your house, and peace be to all that you have. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I hear that you have shearers. Now your shepherds have been with
        us, and we did them no harm, and they missed nothing all the time they were
        in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ask your young men, and they will tell you. Therefore let my young
        men find favor in your eyes, for we come on a feast day. Please give whatever
        you have at hand to your servants and to your son David.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When David\u2019s young men came, they said all this to Nabal in
        the name of David, and then they waited. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Nabal answered David\u2019s servants, \u201CWho is David? Who
        is the son of Jesse? There are many servants these days who are breaking
        away from their masters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shall I take my bread and my water and my meat that I have killed
        for my shearers and give it to men who come from I do not know where?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David\u2019s young men turned away and came back and told him
        all this. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And David said to his men, \u201CEvery man strap on his sword!\u201D
        And every man of them strapped on his sword. David also strapped on his sword.
        And about four hundred men went up after David, while two hundred remained
        with the baggage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But one of the young men told Abigail, Nabal\u2019s wife, \u201CBehold,
        David sent messengers out of the wilderness to greet our master, and he railed
        at them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yet the men were very good to us, and we suffered no harm, and we
        did not miss anything when we were in the fields, as long as we went with
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They were a wall to us both by night and by day, all the while we
        were with them keeping the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now therefore know this and consider what you should do, for harm
        is determined against our master and against all his house, and he is such
        a worthless man that one cannot speak to him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Abigail made haste and took two hundred loaves and two skins
        of wine and five sheep already prepared and five seahs[[COMMENT(0)]] of parched
        grain and a hundred clusters of raisins and two hundred cakes of figs, and
        laid them on donkeys. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:18 '
        content: A was about 7 quarts or 7.3 liters
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And she said to her young men, \u201CGo on before me; behold, I come
        after you.\u201D But she did not tell her husband Nabal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And as she rode on the donkey and came down under cover of the mountain,
        behold, David and his men came down toward her, and she met them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now David had said, \u201CSurely in vain have I guarded all that
        this fellow has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missed of all that
        belonged to him, and he has returned me evil for good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "God do so to the enemies of David[[COMMENT(0)]] and more also, if
        by morning I leave so much as one male of all who belong to him.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:22 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When Abigail saw David, she hurried and got down from the donkey
        and fell before David on her face and bowed to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She fell at his feet and said, \u201COn me alone, my lord, be the
        guilt. Please let your servant speak in your ears, and hear the words of
        your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Let not my lord regard this worthless fellow, Nabal, for as his name
        is, so is he. Nabal[[COMMENT(0)]] is his name, and folly is with him. But
        I your servant did not see the young men of my lord, whom you sent. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:25 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now then, my lord, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, and
        as your soul lives, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has restrained
        you from bloodguilt and from saving with your own hand, now then let your
        enemies and those who seek to do evil to my lord be as Nabal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And now let this present that your servant has brought to my lord
        be given to the young men who follow my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Please forgive the trespass of your servant. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will certainly make my lord a sure house, because my lord is fighting the
        battles of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and evil shall not be found in
        you so long as you live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'If men rise up to pursue you and to seek your life, the life of my
        lord shall be bound in the bundle of the living in the care of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. And the lives of your enemies he shall sling out as from the hollow
        of a sling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done to my lord according
        to all the good that he has spoken concerning you and has appointed you prince[[COMMENT(0)]]
        over Israel, '
      comments:
      - number: '25:30 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "my lord shall have no cause of grief or pangs of conscience for having
        shed blood without cause or for my lord working salvation himself. And when
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has dealt well with my lord, then remember
        your servant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And David said to Abigail, \u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, who sent you this day to meet me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Blessed be your discretion, and blessed be you, who have kept me
        this day from bloodguilt and from working salvation with my own hand! '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For as surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        lives, who has restrained me from hurting you, unless you had hurried and
        come to meet me, truly by morning there had not been left to Nabal so much
        as one male.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then David received from her hand what she had brought him. And he
        said to her, \u201CGo up in peace to your house. See, I have obeyed your
        voice, and I have granted your petition.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Abigail came to Nabal, and behold, he was holding a feast in
        his house, like the feast of a king. And Nabal\u2019s heart was merry within
        him, for he was very drunk. So she told him nothing at all until the morning
        light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In the morning, when the wine had gone out of Nabal, his wife told
        him these things, and his heart died within him, and he became as a stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And about ten days later the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> struck Nabal,
        and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, \u201CBlessed be the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has avenged the insult I received at the
        hand of Nabal, and has kept back his servant from wrongdoing. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has returned the evil of Nabal on his own head.\u201D Then David sent and
        spoke to Abigail, to take her as his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "When the servants of David came to Abigail at Carmel, they said to
        her, \u201CDavid has sent us to you to take you to him as his wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And she rose and bowed with her face to the ground and said, \u201CBehold,
        your handmaid is a servant to wash the feet of the servants of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Abigail hurried and rose and mounted a donkey, and her five young
        women attended her. She followed the messengers of David and became his wife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'David also took Ahinoam of Jezreel, and both of them became his wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Saul had given Michal his daughter, David\u2019s wife, to Palti the
        son of Laish, who was of Gallim."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Spares Saul Again'
      title: David Spares Saul Again
      number: 1
      content: "    Then the Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs not
        David hiding himself on the hill of Hachilah, which is on the east of Jeshimon?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Saul arose and went down to the wilderness of Ziph with three
        thousand chosen men of Israel to seek David in the wilderness of Ziph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Saul encamped on the hill of Hachilah, which is beside the road
        on the east of Jeshimon. But David remained in the wilderness. When he saw
        that Saul came after him into the wilderness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David sent out spies and learned that Saul had indeed come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then David rose and came to the place where Saul had encamped. And
        David saw the place where Saul lay, with Abner the son of Ner, the commander
        of his army. Saul was lying within the encampment, while the army was encamped
        around him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David said to Ahimelech the Hittite, and to Joab\u2019s brother
        Abishai the son of Zeruiah, \u201CWho will go down with me into the camp
        to Saul?\u201D And Abishai said, \u201CI will go down with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David and Abishai went to the army by night. And there lay Saul
        sleeping within the encampment, with his spear stuck in the ground at his
        head, and Abner and the army lay around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abishai said to David, \u201CGod has given your enemy into your
        hand this day. Now please let me pin him to the earth with one stroke of
        the spear, and I will not strike him twice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David said to Abishai, \u201CDo not destroy him, for who can
        put out his hand against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed
        and be guiltless?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And David said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike him, or his day will come to die,
        or he will go down into battle and perish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forbid that I should put out my hand
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed. But take now the
        spear that is at his head and the jar of water, and let us go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David took the spear and the jar of water from Saul\u2019s head,
        and they went away. No man saw it or knew it, nor did any awake, for they
        were all asleep, because a deep sleep from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had fallen upon them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David went over to the other side and stood far off on the top
        of the hill, with a great space between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And David called to the army, and to Abner the son of Ner, saying,
        \u201CWill you not answer, Abner?\u201D Then Abner answered, \u201CWho are
        you who calls to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And David said to Abner, \u201CAre you not a man? Who is like you
        in Israel? Why then have you not kept watch over your lord the king? For
        one of the people came in to destroy the king your lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This thing that you have done is not good. As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, you deserve to die, because you have not kept watch over your lord,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed. And now see where the king\u2019s
        spear is and the jar of water that was at his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Saul recognized David\u2019s voice and said, \u201CIs this your voice,
        my son David?\u201D And David said, \u201CIt is my voice, my lord, O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhy does my lord pursue after his servant? For
        what have I done? What evil is on my hands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore let my lord the king hear the words of his servant.
        If it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has stirred you up against me,
        may he accept an offering, but if it is men, may they be cursed before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for they have driven me out this day that I
        should have no share in the heritage of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, \u2018Go, serve other gods.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now therefore, let not my blood fall to the earth away from the presence
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for the king of Israel has come out to
        seek a single flea like one who hunts a partridge in the mountains.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CI have sinned. Return, my son David, for I
        will no more do you harm, because my life was precious in your eyes this
        day. Behold, I have acted foolishly, and have made a great mistake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David answered and said, \u201CHere is the spear, O king! Let
        one of the young men come over and take it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rewards every man for his righteousness
        and his faithfulness, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave you into my
        hand today, and I would not put out my hand against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Behold, as your life was precious this day in my sight, so may my
        life be precious in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and may
        he deliver me out of all tribulation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CBlessed be you, my son David! You
        will do many things and will succeed in them.\u201D So David went his way,
        and Saul returned to his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Flees to the Philistines'
      title: David Flees to the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David said in his heart, \u201CNow I shall perish one day
        by the hand of Saul. There is nothing better for me than that I should escape
        to the land of the Philistines. Then Saul will despair of seeking me any
        longer within the borders of Israel, and I shall escape out of his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David arose and went over, he and the six hundred men who were
        with him, to Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David lived with Achish at Gath, he and his men, every man with
        his household, and David with his two wives, Ahinoam of Jezreel, and Abigail
        of Carmel, Nabal\u2019s widow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when it was told Saul that David had fled to Gath, he no longer
        sought him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said to Achish, \u201CIf I have found favor in your eyes,
        let a place be given me in one of the country towns, that I may dwell there.
        For why should your servant dwell in the royal city with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So that day Achish gave him Ziklag. Therefore Ziklag has belonged
        to the kings of Judah to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the number of the days that David lived in the country of the
        Philistines was a year and four months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now David and his men went up and made raids against the Geshurites,
        the Girzites, and the Amalekites, for these were the inhabitants of the land
        from of old, as far as Shur, to the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And David would strike the land and would leave neither man nor woman
        alive, but would take away the sheep, the oxen, the donkeys, the camels,
        and the garments, and come back to Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When Achish asked, \u201CWhere have you made a raid today?\u201D
        David would say, \u201CAgainst the Negeb of Judah,\u201D or, \u201CAgainst
        the Negeb of the Jerahmeelites,\u201D or, \u201CAgainst the Negeb of the
        Kenites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And David would leave neither man nor woman alive to bring news to
        Gath, thinking, \u201Clest they should tell about us and say, \u2018So David
        has done.\u2019\u201D Such was his custom all the while he lived in the country
        of the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Achish trusted David, thinking, \u201CHe has made himself an
        utter stench to his people Israel; therefore he shall always be my servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul and the Medium of En-dor'
      title: Saul and the Medium of En-dor
      number: 1
      content: "  In those days the Philistines gathered their forces for war, to
        fight against Israel. And Achish said to David, \u201CUnderstand that you
        and your men are to go out with me in the army.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said to Achish, \u201CVery well, you shall know what your servant
        can do.\u201D And Achish said to David, \u201CVery well, I will make you
        my bodyguard for life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had mourned for him and buried
        him in Ramah, his own city. And Saul had put the mediums and the necromancers
        out of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Philistines assembled and came and encamped at Shunem. And Saul
        gathered all Israel, and they encamped at Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Saul saw the army of the Philistines, he was afraid, and his
        heart trembled greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Saul inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        did not answer him, either by dreams, or by Urim, or by prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servants, \u201CSeek out for me a woman who
        is a medium, that I may go to her and inquire of her.\u201D And his servants
        said to him, \u201CBehold, there is a medium at En-dor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Saul disguised himself and put on other garments and went, he
        and two men with him. And they came to the woman by night. And he said, \u201CDivine
        for me by a spirit and bring up for me whomever I shall name to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The woman said to him, \u201CSurely you know what Saul has done,
        how he has cut off the mediums and the necromancers from the land. Why then
        are you laying a trap for my life to bring about my death?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Saul swore to her by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CAs
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, no punishment shall come upon you
        for this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the woman said, \u201CWhom shall I bring up for you?\u201D He
        said, \u201CBring up Samuel for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out with a loud voice. And the
        woman said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you deceived me? You are Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The king said to her, \u201CDo not be afraid. What do you see?\u201D
        And the woman said to Saul, \u201CI see a god coming up out of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said to her, \u201CWhat is his appearance?\u201D And she said,
        \u201CAn old man is coming up, and he is wrapped in a robe.\u201D And Saul
        knew that it was Samuel, and he bowed with his face to the ground and paid
        homage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you disturbed me by bringing
        me up?\u201D Saul answered, \u201CI am in great distress, for the Philistines
        are warring against me, and God has turned away from me and answers me no
        more, either by prophets or by dreams. Therefore I have summoned you to tell
        me what I shall do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CWhy then do you ask me, since the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has turned from you and become your enemy? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done to you as he spoke by me,
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has torn the kingdom out of your hand
        and given it to your neighbor, David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because you did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and did not carry out his fierce wrath against Amalek, therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has done this thing to you this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Moreover, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give Israel also with
        you into the hand of the Philistines, and tomorrow you and your sons shall
        be with me. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give the army of Israel
        also into the hand of the Philistines.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Saul fell at once full length on the ground, filled with fear
        because of the words of Samuel. And there was no strength in him, for he
        had eaten nothing all day and all night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the woman came to Saul, and when she saw that he was terrified,
        she said to him, \u201CBehold, your servant has obeyed you. I have taken
        my life in my hand and have listened to what you have said to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now therefore, you also obey your servant. Let me set a morsel of
        bread before you; and eat, that you may have strength when you go on your
        way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He refused and said, \u201CI will not eat.\u201D But his servants,
        together with the woman, urged him, and he listened to their words. So he
        arose from the earth and sat on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now the woman had a fattened calf in the house, and she quickly killed
        it, and she took flour and kneaded it and baked unleavened bread of it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: and she put it before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then they
        rose and went away that night.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines Reject David'
      title: The Philistines Reject David
      number: 1
      content: '    Now the Philistines had gathered all their forces at Aphek. And
        the Israelites were encamped by the spring that is in Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As the lords of the Philistines were passing on by hundreds and by
        thousands, and David and his men were passing on in the rear with Achish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "the commanders of the Philistines said, \u201CWhat are these Hebrews
        doing here?\u201D And Achish said to the commanders of the Philistines, \u201CIs
        this not David, the servant of Saul, king of Israel, who has been with me
        now for days and years, and since he deserted to me I have found no fault
        in him to this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the commanders of the Philistines were angry with him. And the
        commanders of the Philistines said to him, \u201CSend the man back, that
        he may return to the place to which you have assigned him. He shall not go
        down with us to battle, lest in the battle he become an adversary to us.
        For how could this fellow reconcile himself to his lord? Would it not be
        with the heads of the men here? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is not this David, of whom they sing to one another in dances,  \u2018Saul
        has struck down his thousands,and David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Achish called David and said to him, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, you have been honest, and to me it seems right that you should march
        out and in with me in the campaign. For I have found nothing wrong in you
        from the day of your coming to me to this day. Nevertheless, the lords do
        not approve of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So go back now; and go peaceably, that you may not displease the
        lords of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David said to Achish, \u201CBut what have I done? What have you
        found in your servant from the day I entered your service until now, that
        I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Achish answered David and said, \u201CI know that you are as
        blameless in my sight as an angel of God. Nevertheless, the commanders of
        the Philistines have said, \u2018He shall not go up with us to the battle.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now then rise early in the morning with the servants of your lord
        who came with you, and start early in the morning, and depart as soon as
        you have light.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So David set out with his men early in the morning to return to the
        land of the Philistines. But the Philistines went up to Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Wives Are Captured"
      title: "David\u2019s Wives Are Captured"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when David and his men came to Ziklag on the third day, the
        Amalekites had made a raid against the Negeb and against Ziklag. They had
        overcome Ziklag and burned it with fire '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and taken captive the women and all[[COMMENT(0)]] who were in it,
        both small and great. They killed no one, but carried them off and went their
        way. '
      comments:
      - number: '30:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when David and his men came to the city, they found it burned
        with fire, and their wives and sons and daughters taken captive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and the people who were with him raised their voices and
        wept until they had no more strength to weep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David\u2019s two wives also had been taken captive, Ahinoam of Jezreel
        and Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David was greatly distressed, for the people spoke of stoning
        him, because all the people were bitter in soul,[[COMMENT(0)]] each for his
        sons and daughters. But David strengthened himself in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:6 '
        content: Compare 22:2
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  And David said to Abiathar the priest, the son of Ahimelech, \u201CBring
        me the ephod.\u201D So Abiathar brought the ephod to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CShall
        I pursue after this band? Shall I overtake them?\u201D He answered him, \u201CPursue,
        for you shall surely overtake and shall surely rescue.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David set out, and the six hundred men who were with him, and
        they came to the brook Besor, where those who were left behind stayed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But David pursued, he and four hundred men. Two hundred stayed behind,
        who were too exhausted to cross the brook Besor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They found an Egyptian in the open country and brought him to David.
        And they gave him bread and he ate. They gave him water to drink, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they gave him a piece of a cake of figs and two clusters of raisins.
        And when he had eaten, his spirit revived, for he had not eaten bread or
        drunk water for three days and three nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CTo whom do you belong? And where are
        you from?\u201D He said, \u201CI am a young man of Egypt, servant to an Amalekite,
        and my master left me behind because I fell sick three days ago. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We had made a raid against the Negeb of the Cherethites and against
        that which belongs to Judah and against the Negeb of Caleb, and we burned
        Ziklag with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: David Defeats the Amalekites'
      title: David Defeats the Amalekites
      number: 15
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CWill you take me down to this band?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CSwear to me by God that you will not kill me or deliver
        me into the hands of my master, and I will take you down to this band.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when he had taken him down, behold, they were spread abroad over
        all the land, eating and drinking and dancing, because of all the great spoil
        they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And David struck them down from twilight until the evening of the
        next day, and not a man of them escaped, except four hundred young men, who
        mounted camels and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'David recovered all that the Amalekites had taken, and David rescued
        his two wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Nothing was missing, whether small or great, sons or daughters, spoil
        or anything that had been taken. David brought back all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "David also captured all the flocks and herds, and the people drove
        the livestock before him,[[COMMENT(0)]] and said, \u201CThis is David\u2019s
        spoil.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:20 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew clause is uncertain
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then David came to the two hundred men who had been too exhausted
        to follow David, and who had been left at the brook Besor. And they went
        out to meet David and to meet the people who were with him. And when David
        came near to the people he greeted them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then all the wicked and worthless fellows among the men who had gone
        with David said, \u201CBecause they did not go with us, we will not give
        them any of the spoil that we have recovered, except that each man may lead
        away his wife and children, and depart.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But David said, \u201CYou shall not do so, my brothers, with what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given us. He has preserved us and given
        into our hand the band that came against us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Who would listen to you in this matter? For as his share is who goes
        down into the battle, so shall his share be who stays by the baggage. They
        shall share alike.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he made it a statute and a rule for Israel from that day forward
        to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When David came to Ziklag, he sent part of the spoil to his friends,
        the elders of Judah, saying, \u201CHere is a present for you from the spoil
        of the enemies of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It was for those in Bethel, in Ramoth of the Negeb, in Jattir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'in Aroer, in Siphmoth, in Eshtemoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in Racal, in the cities of the Jerahmeelites, in the cities of the
        Kenites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in Hormah, in Bor-ashan, in Athach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: in Hebron, for all the places where David and his men had roamed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Saul'
      title: The Death of Saul
      number: 1
      content: '    Now the Philistines were fighting against Israel, and the men
        of Israel fled before the Philistines and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Philistines overtook Saul and his sons, and the Philistines
        struck down Jonathan and Abinadab and Malchi-shua, the sons of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The battle pressed hard against Saul, and the archers found him,
        and he was badly wounded by the archers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Saul said to his armor-bearer, \u201CDraw your sword, and thrust
        me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and thrust me through,
        and mistreat me.\u201D But his armor-bearer would not, for he feared greatly.
        Therefore Saul took his own sword and fell upon it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when his armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell upon
        his sword and died with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus Saul died, and his three sons, and his armor-bearer, and all
        his men, on the same day together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley
        and those beyond the Jordan saw that the men of Israel had fled and that
        Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned their cities and fled. And the
        Philistines came and lived in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, they
        found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So they cut off his head and stripped off his armor and sent messengers
        throughout the land of the Philistines, to carry the good news to the house
        of their idols and to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They put his armor in the temple of Ashtaroth, and they fastened
        his body to the wall of Beth-shan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead heard what the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the valiant men arose and went all night and took the body of
        Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth-shan, and they came
        to Jabesh and burned them there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And they took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree
        in Jabesh and fasted seven days.
      comments: []
